steps.Step 1: Whisk soy sauce, mirin, olive oil, honey, sesame oil, garlic powder, ginger, lemon juice, and Worcestershire sauce together in a bowl. Transfer 1/4 of the marinade to a small bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
steps.Step 2: Place remaining marinade in a zip-top bag and add chicken. Marinate in the refrigerator for 8 hours, or overnight.
steps.Step 3: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Remove chicken from the refrigerator.
steps.Step 4: Combine bell peppers, onion, and zucchini in a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper, and toss to coat.
steps.Step 5: Make the kabobs by alternating chicken with bell peppers, pineapple, onion, and zucchini. Drizzle some of the sauce from the zip-top bag onto the kabobs.
steps.Step 6: Cook on the preheated grill, turning every few minutes and drizzling any remaining sauce from the bag over top, until no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, 15 to 20 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).
steps.Step 7: About 10 minutes before the skewers are done, mix cold water and cornstarch in a small bowl. Put the 1/4 cup reserved marinade in a small saucepan over medium heat. When hot, add cornstarch-water mixture and reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens, 7 to 8 minutes.
steps.Step 8: Place kabobs on a tray and drizzle with thickened teriyaki sauce. Sprinkle toasted sesame seeds on top.

2201.title: Irish Stout Beef Stew
2201.description: A twist on traditional Irish stew, this recipe adds extra seasonings to avoid blandness.  Serve with Irish soda bread for a complete meal.

steps.Step 1: Place potatoes, onion, garlic, green beans, and tomato paste in a slow cooker.
steps.Step 2: Sprinkle with stew seasoning and pour beef broth over top. Mix in stew seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
steps.Step 3: Heat oil in a medium skillet over medium-high heat.
steps.Step 4: Place flour on a plate and add seasoned salt. Coat stew meat in the flour mixture then brown in the hot skillet, 5 to 7 minutes per batch.
steps.Step 5: Add browned meat directly to the slow cooker.
steps.Step 6: Add stout beer to the slow cooker and water, if necessary, to bring the liquid even with the ingredients so nothing dries out.
steps.Step 7: Cook on High until meat is tender and potatoes are soft, about 6 hours.

2208.title: Easy Baked Mostaccioli
2208.description: A simple and hearty mostaccioli pasta dish, perfect for a quick weeknight meal.  The dish is easily baked in a disposable aluminum pan for easy cleanup.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
steps.Step 2: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook mostaccioli in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, 8 to 10 minutes. Drain.
steps.Step 3: Meanwhile, heat a nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Cook and stir ground beef until browned and crumbly, 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from the heat. Drain and discard grease. Add spaghetti sauce to the pan and mix with the beef.
steps.Step 4: Transfer beef mixture to the prepared baking dish. Spread evenly over the bottom and layer cooked pasta over top. Sprinkle with mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Cover with foil.
steps.Step 5: Bake in the preheated oven for 40 minutes. Remove foil and continue to bake until cheese is melted and lightly browned, about 10 more minutes.

2213.title: Grilled Chicken Satay
2213.description: Fire up the grill for this Indonesian-inspired chicken satay. Skewers of perfectly cooked chicken are served with a fresh and flavourful peanut sauce. So delicious that no one will be able to have just one!

steps.Step 1: Put wooden skewers in a shallow dish and cover with water. Let soak for 20 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Place chicken strips into a bowl. Combine soy sauce, tomato sauce, peanut oil, garlic, pepper, and cumin in a small bowl; mix to combine. Pour over chicken strips and mix so chicken is well coated on all sides. Marinate for 15 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Meanwhile, make the peanut sauce. Add 1 tablespoon oil to a hot skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic. Cook and stir until onion is soft and translucent, about 4 minutes. Add peanut butter, sugar, soy sauce, and water. Mix well. Cook until sauce has thickened slightly, about 5 minutes. Add lemon juice and remove from heat.
steps.Step 4: Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil the grate. Thread each chicken strip onto a skewer.
steps.Step 5: Place skewers on the preheated grill and cook for a total of 10 minutes, flipping once halfway through cooking. Serve the satay skewers immediately with the peanut sauce for dipping.

2215.title: Holiday Hot Spinach Dip
2215.description: A yummy hot vegetable dip, perfect served with crackers.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Mix together spinach, bell pepper, garlic, artichokes, sour cream, and parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 3: Mixture will be thick; add cream to thin to dip consistency.
steps.Step 4: Spoon into a 1-quart baking dish.
steps.Step 5: Bake for 20 minutes, or until bubbly. Serve with crackers.

2250.title: Norwegian Cabbage Rolls
2250.description: A delicious take on traditional Norwegian kålruletter.  The recipe uses a flavorful filling of ground beef, rice, and caraway seeds, rolled in cabbage leaves and baked until tender. Served with brown gravy, rice, and potatoes, with a side of cucumber salad.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a baking pan.
steps.Step 2: Heat butter in a skillet over medium heat; stir in onion. Cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Transfer onion to a large mixing bowl and add beef, cooked rice, cream, egg, parsley, potato starch, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper, caraway seeds, ginger, nutmeg, and cloves. Mix to combine in an even consistency and refrigerate filling until needed.
steps.Step 4: Bring a large pot of generously salted water to a boil. Place 1 head of cabbage in the boiling water and parboil until bright green and leaves are softened, about 2 minutes. Carefully remove cabbage with tongs or a large fork. Repeat with remaining head of cabbage. Allow to cool, about 10 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Remove outer leaves from the cooled cabbage. Lay 1 leaf flat on a work surface and cut out the stem. Spoon a generous 2 tablespoons of filling into the center of the leaf. Fold the corners at the stem end diagonally over the filling, fold the sides over, and roll up like a tiny burrito. Place in the prepared baking pan. Repeat to make remaining cabbage rolls until filling is used up.
steps.Step 6: Add water to the baking pan until it is halfway up the sides of the cabbage rolls.
steps.Step 7: Bake in the preheated oven until beef is cooked through and no longer pink, about 40 minutes.

2256.title: Jalapeno Popper Chicken Baked Ziti
2256.description: A delicious, spicy, and creamy baked pasta dish featuring shredded chicken, jalapeno popper filling, and ziti pasta. The recipe combines the flavors of classic jalapeno poppers with baked ziti.

steps.Step 1: Combine chicken breasts, chicken broth, salt, pepper, onion flakes, oregano, and garlic in a medium slow cooker, ensuring the chicken is fully covered by broth.
steps.Step 2: Cook until chicken is no longer pink in the center, on Low for 5 to 6 hours or on High for 3 to 4 hours.
steps.Step 3: Thirty minutes before chicken is finished cooking, preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.
steps.Step 4: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add ziti and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 11 minutes. Drain and set aside.
steps.Step 5: While ziti is cooking, prepare filling: fry bacon, jalapenos, and onion in a small skillet over medium-high heat until onions are tender and bacon is browned, 5 to 7 minutes. Remove from heat and transfer to a small mixing bowl with cream cheese, mozzarella, Parmesan, and mayonnaise; mix until well combined.
steps.Step 6: Remove chicken from the slow cooker and place into a large bowl; use 2 forks to shred chicken into small pieces. Add cooked ziti and Alfredo sauce; mix well.
steps.Step 7: Pour 1/2 of the chicken-ziti mixture into the prepared baking dish and sprinkle pepper Jack cheese in an even layer over top. Spread jalapeno popper filling evenly across the dish. Pour remaining chicken-ziti mixture into the dish, and sprinkle 1/2 cup mozzarella over top.
steps.Step 8: Mix crushed crackers, Parmesan cheese, and butter for topping together in a small bowl; sprinkle over the pasta dish.
steps.Step 9: Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted and just barely starts to turn golden, 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from the oven and serve immediately.

2360.title: Baked Feta Pasta
2360.description: An easy pasta dish inspired by TikTok trends, featuring baked feta, cherry tomatoes, and vegetables. The dish offers a flavorful tomato-based sauce with a creamy texture from the feta.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Combine cherry tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, olive oil, garlic, lemon juice, lemon zest, red pepper flakes, black pepper, Italian seasoning, basil, and sea salt in a 13x9-inch baking dish.
steps.Step 3: Make room in the middle of the pan and add block of feta cheese. Flip in oil, making sure cheese remains intact and becomes well coated.
steps.Step 4: Bake in the preheated oven until the cherry tomatoes begin to blister and split, 40 to 45 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Meanwhile, bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add penne and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 11 minutes. Drain and reserve about 1 cup of the pasta water.
steps.Step 6: Remove feta-tomato mixture from the oven. Mash garlic, tomatoes, onions, and peppers with a heavy spoon and mix with the feta cheese, creating a sauce.
steps.Step 7: Stir in spinach and cooked pasta. The spinach will get cooked from the heat of the pasta sauce and pasta. Add pasta water, a little at a time if needed, to reach desired consistency.
steps.Step 8: Mix well and serve.

2366.title: Crispy Rosemary Sea Salt Flatbread Crackers
2366.description: These crispy rosemary sea salt flatbread crackers are easy to make at home and can be customized with different herbs and spices. They are a great accompaniment to soups, dips, or smoked fish.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with a silicon mat or parchment paper.
steps.Step 2: Place flour, salt, sugar, and grated cheese in a mixing bowl. Stir together until well mixed. Add rosemary; drizzle with olive oil and add water. Mix with a fork until mixture comes together in a fairly sticky dough and pulls away from the sides of the bowl, 3 to 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Transfer dough onto floured surface and add flour as you knead the dough. Knead until it no longer sticks to work surface, 4 to 5 minutes. Divide dough in half.
steps.Step 4: Dust work surface with flour. Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness or less. Brush or mist surface of dough very lightly with water. Sprinkle with coarse sea salt. Prick the entire surface of dough with the tines of a fork to prevent crackers from puffing too much when baking.
steps.Step 5: Cut each rolled out half into about 30 pieces with a pizza wheel. You can cut them out in squares, rectangles, or triangles--your choice. Transfer onto prepared baking sheet with a bench scraper or your floured fingers (dough will be very sticky).
steps.Step 6: Bake in preheated oven until perfectly browned and crunchy, 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the thickness.

2385.title: Whole Wheat Blueberry Beet Muffins
2385.description: These muffins combine whole wheat flour, rolled oats, and fresh blueberries with shredded beets for a unique flavor and texture.  A blend of dry and wet ingredients are combined to create a moist and delicious muffin.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease 24 muffin cups.
steps.Step 2: Mix the whole wheat flour, rolled oats, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt in a large bowl.
steps.Step 3: In a separate bowl, mix the canola oil, applesauce, sugar, eggs, and water.
steps.Step 4: Pour the applesauce mixture into the dry ingredients, and stir to combine.
steps.Step 5: Gently fold in the blueberries and shredded beats.
steps.Step 6: Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin cups.
steps.Step 7: Bake in the preheated oven until browned and a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.

2429.title: Mixed Seafood Curry
2429.description: A delicious and flavorful mixed seafood curry, perfect for a weeknight dinner.  The curry features shrimp, scallops, and asparagus in a rich coconut milk sauce.

steps.Step 1: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Saute onion, ginger, and garlic in hot oil until onion starts to soften, 2 to 3 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Stir coconut milk, lime juice, curry paste, and brown sugar into onion mixture, bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Stir shrimp, scallops, asparagus, cilantro, and salt into onion mixture; cook until shrimp and scallops are no longer transparent in the center, about 5 minutes.

2438.title: Chipotle Crusted Pork Tenderloin
2438.description: Sweet and spicy rub for pork tenderloins. Just coat, let stand for 20 minutes and grill! Goes great with polenta or mashed yams.

steps.Step 1: Preheat grill for medium-high heat.
steps.Step 2: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the onion powder, garlic powder, chipotle chile powder, salt, and brown sugar. Place tenderloins in bag and shake, coating meat evenly. Refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Lightly oil grill grate, and arrange meat on grate.
steps.Step 4: Cook for 20 minutes, turning meat every 5 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Remove from grill, let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

2472.title: Grilled Asian Ginger Pork Chops
2472.description: These grilled pork chops are infused with a flavorful Asian marinade that includes ginger, orange juice, and soy sauce. The marinade is designed to tenderize and add depth of flavor to the pork. Perfect for a hot summer evening, these chops pair well with grilled vegetables.

steps.Step 1: In a shallow container, mix together orange juice, soy sauce, ginger, orange zest, garlic, chile paste, and salt.
steps.Step 2: Add pork chops, and turn to coat evenly.
steps.Step 3: Cover, and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, or overnight. Turn the pork chops in the marinade occasionally.
steps.Step 4: Preheat grill for high heat, and lightly oil grate.
steps.Step 5: Grill pork chops for 5 to 6 minutes per side, or to desired doneness.

2507.title: Birria
2507.description: A flavorful Mexican-style shredded beef soup made with a blend of dried chiles. Serve with cilantro, onions, cabbage, and tortillas.

ingredients.name: New Mexico dried red chile pods

steps.Step 1: Place dried chiles into a saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer until chiles are softened, 15 to 20 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Pour chile mixture into a blender. Add garlic, onion slice, pepper, oregano, cumin, and cinnamon. Blend until smooth.
steps.Step 3: Layer chopped onions in the bottom of a slow cooker. Place chuck roast over onions and add bay leaves. Pour chile sauce on top.
steps.Step 4: Cook on High until beef is tender enough to shred with a fork, about 5 hours.
steps.Step 5: Remove beef from sauce. Continue cooking sauce until reduced, 35 to 45 minutes. Return beef to sauce and season with salt.

2526.title: Dutch Oven Chili Colorado
2526.description: A hearty chili colorado recipe made in a Dutch oven, featuring beef and a blend of chiles.  The recipe is adapted from The Complete Meat Cookbook and skips beans and tomatoes.

ingredients.name: salt and freshly ground black pepper

steps.Step 1: Soak the ancho chiles in boiling hot water to cover for 1 hour.
steps.Step 2: While dried chiles soak, preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Season beef with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 3: Heat a cast iron Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Brown the beef on all sides, working in small batches, 5 to 7 minutes. Set aside.
steps.Step 4: Drain chiles; remove stems and seeds. Place chiles, onions, garlic, ground chile pepper, salt, cumin seeds, oregano, and coriander in the bowl of a food processor. Pulse to chop, then process into a thick paste. Add 1 cup beer and continue processing to blend.
steps.Step 5: Place meat and any accumulated juices back in the Dutch oven, pour in sauce, and stir well. Cover with a sheet of aluminum foil, then place lid on top for a tight seal.
steps.Step 6: Bake on the middle rack of the preheated oven for 1 hour; stir. Continue to bake, stirring every 15 minutes, until meat is fork-tender, 30 minutes to 1 hour more, adding more beer if sauce seems too thick.

2540.title: Pressure Cooker Beef Chili
2540.description: A flavorful and easy beef chili recipe, perfect for a quick weeknight meal.  The pressure cooker method ensures tender beef and a rich, flavorful chili in a fraction of the time compared to traditional stovetop methods.

ingredients.name: diced tomatoes with green chile peppers

steps.Step 1: Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Season beef generously with salt and black pepper; place meat in the skillet and cook until brown on all sides, 5 to 10 minutes. Transfer to plate and set aside.
steps.Step 2: Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil over medium-low heat in the pot of a pressure cooker. Stir onion and garlic into pot; cook until almost translucent, 4 to 6 minutes. Stir in ancho chile powder, paprika, cumin, black pepper, chipotle chile powder, cayenne pepper, and oregano; cook until fragrant, 2 minutes. Add diced tomatoes, beef, and water; stir to combine.
steps.Step 3: Lock the lid of your pressure cooker. Increase heat to high and bring to full pressure. Reduce heat to low to maintain pressure; cook for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let rest 10 minutes. Ensure that pressure is fully released and remove the lid.
steps.Step 4: Return uncovered pressure cooker to burner over high heat. Stir in corn chips and bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes. Garnish with cilantro and green onion.

2544.title: Healthier Lemon Poppy Seed Donuts
2544.description: These donuts are made with Swerve® and almond milk. They are baked, rather than fried, making them a healthier alternative to traditional donuts.  They are delicious, quick, and easy to make.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray 2 donut pans with nonstick cooking spray.
steps.Step 2: Place granulated sugar substitute and lemon zest in a bowl. Mix until zest is fully coated with sugar. Add egg, butter, lemon juice, vanilla, and lemon extract. Add almond milk and mix until well incorporated.
steps.Step 3: Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together. Add to the sugar mixture. Fold in poppy seeds. Divide the batter evenly among the donut pans.
steps.Step 4: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into a donut comes out clean, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool in the pans for 10 minutes. Remove from the pans and cool completely.
steps.Step 5: While the donuts cool, make the icing. Mix powder sugar substitute, lemon juice, almond milk, lemon zest, vanilla, and salt together in a bowl. Set a rack over a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper. Dip donuts into the icing and place on the rack until glaze sets, 2 to 3 minutes.

2551.title: Breeze Banana Bread
2551.description: This classic banana bread features a delicious flavor and texture, enhanced by the addition of Almond Breeze almond milk and almond flour.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F and coat 2 mini loaf pans with nonstick spray.
steps.Step 2: Whisk together bananas, sugar, Almond Breeze, oil, extract, and egg in a large bowl.
steps.Step 3: Stir together dry ingredients and add to banana mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are incorporated.
steps.Step 4: Spoon equal amounts into prepared pans and bake for 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
steps.Step 5: Let cool before removing from pans.

2583.title: Flax Seed Zucchini Bread
2583.description: A healthier version of zucchini bread, using less sugar and oil, and incorporating flax seeds. It's a delicious treat.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Whisk together the all-purpose flour, soy flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, and cinnamon in a bowl until blended; set aside.
steps.Step 2: Place the tofu in a blender, and puree until smooth. Scrape into a bowl, and beat with the eggs, honey, brown sugar, walnut oil, and almond extract until smooth.
steps.Step 3: Stir in the flour mixture until just moistened, then stir in the zucchini, pineapple, walnuts, and flax seed until combined.
steps.Step 4: Divide this batter between two 8x4 inch ungreased loaf pans.
steps.Step 5: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaves comes out clean, about 1 hour.
steps.Step 6: Cool in the pans on a wire rack before slicing.

2595.title: Winter Vegetable Hash
2595.description: A hearty and flavorful dish featuring a medley of winter vegetables, cooked in a flavorful blend of olive oil and butter. The combination of potatoes, mushrooms, bell pepper, squash, and kale provides a satisfying and comforting meal.

steps.Step 1: Place oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Melt butter and mix in potatoes, mushrooms, pepper, squash, and shallot. Season with garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
steps.Step 2: Cook 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender.
steps.Step 3: Mix kale and sage into skillet. Continue cooking 5 minutes, until kale is wilted. Serve and enjoy!

2632.title: Cauliflower Clam Chowder
2632.description: This healthier take on clam chowder has fewer calories and less saturated fat than the original. Puréed cauliflower and potatoes keep it creamy while celery leaves and lemon zest balance each bite. Other healthy swaps: turkey bacon and low-sodium chicken broth replace regular bacon and clam juice.

steps.Step 1: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add turkey bacon and cook until crisp, 4 to 6 minutes. Transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate to drain, reserving drippings in the saucepan.
steps.Step 2: Add onion and celery to the saucepan; cook over medium heat until onion is translucent, about 4 minutes. Add garlic; cook, stirring, 30 seconds more. Add chicken broth and potato; bring to a boil.
steps.Step 3: Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes. Add cauliflower and salt; simmer, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are just tender, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Working in 2 batches, transfer cooked vegetable mixture to a blender. Add milk and blend until very smooth, about 2 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Stir mixture back into the saucepan. Bring to a gentle simmer to heat through, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in clams and lemon zest.
steps.Step 6: Sprinkle servings with pepper, bacon, and celery leaves.

2635.title: Air Fryer Blueberry Muffins
2635.description: These blueberry muffins are baked in an air fryer, making them a quick and easy treat without heating up the entire kitchen.  A simple recipe that's perfect for a quick breakfast or snack.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the air fryer to 340 degrees F (170 degrees C) for 5 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Combine flour, sugar, and cinnamon in a bowl. Add milk, melted butter, egg, and vanilla extract. Blend until well combined.
steps.Step 3: Fold in blueberries. Add mixture to silicone cupcake liners using a small scoop, filling each 3/4 way full.
steps.Step 4: Place carefully into the air fryer basket.
steps.Step 5: Air fry muffins for 14 minutes.

2720.title: Vegan Red Lentil Soup
2720.description: A creamy and delicious vegan red lentil soup.  A hearty and flavorful soup perfect for a chilly evening.

steps.Step 1: Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onion, ginger, garlic, and fenugreek; cook and stir until onion is tender.
steps.Step 2: Add lentils, squash, and cilantro, then stir in water, coconut milk, and tomato paste. Season with curry powder, cayenne pepper, nutmeg, salt, and pepper; bring to a boil.
steps.Step 3: Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes, or until lentils and squash are tender.

2759.title: Dark Chocolate Beet Cake
2759.description: A great option for sneaking veggies into a dessert, this dark chocolate beet cake is irresistible for chocolate lovers.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease the bottom of a 10-inch round cake pan.
steps.Step 2: Puree beets in a food processor or blender until the consistency is smooth and no lumps remain. Add eggs and blend for a few seconds more.
steps.Step 3: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and baking soda together in a separate bowl with an electric mixer. Mix in butter.
steps.Step 4: Pour beet puree into the bowl while mixing on low speed to combine. Pour batter into the prepared pan.
steps.Step 5: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 40 minutes. Cool in the pan for 5 to 10 minutes before inverting onto a wire rack and cooling completely.

2773.title: Corn Dog Muffins
2773.description: Corn dog muffins are an easy way to make a version of the popular fair treat. You can substitute cocktail wieners for hot dogs.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Lightly grease muffin tins.
steps.Step 2: Stir cornbread mix and brown sugar together in a large bowl. Whisk eggs and milk in a small bowl until smooth.
steps.Step 3: Fold eggs and cheese into cornbread mixture until moistened.
steps.Step 4: Spoon mixture into muffin tins about 2/3 full. Add 1 hot dog half to each muffin.
steps.Step 5: Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 14 to 18 minutes.

2783.title: Sweet Bacon Corn Bread
2783.description: A delicious twist on classic cornbread, incorporating sweet bacon for a unique flavor profile. Perfect as a side dish or a satisfying snack.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Arrange bacon in a Reynolds® Bakeware Bacon Pan.
steps.Step 2: Bake for 8 minutes, until almost crisp. Drizzle the bacon with 1 tablespoon maple syrup and bake 4 to 6 minutes more or until glazed. Cook longer for crispier bacon. Cool and chop.
steps.Step 3: Stir together the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl.
steps.Step 4: In a small bowl, whisk together milk, eggs, butter and remaining 4 tablespoons maple syrup.
steps.Step 5: Add the milk mixture all at once to the cornmeal mixture. Add the chopped bacon. Stir just until moistened.
steps.Step 6: Pour the batter into an 8x8-inch Reynolds® Bakeware Pan.
steps.Step 7: Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Let cool slightly before serving.
steps.Step 8: Drizzle with additional maple syrup, if desired.

2785.title: Spanish Rice Bake
2785.description: A savory rice dish featuring ground beef, onions, bell peppers, tomatoes, and a sweet-hot sauce. It's baked with Cheddar cheese and garnished with cilantro.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Brown the ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Drain excess fat and transfer beef to a large pot over medium low heat.
steps.Step 3: Stir in the onion, green bell pepper, tomatoes, water, rice, chile sauce, salt, brown sugar, cumin, Worcestershire sauce and ground black pepper.
steps.Step 4: Let this simmer for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, then transport this to a 2-quart casserole dish.
steps.Step 5: Press down firmly and sprinkle with the shredded Cheddar cheese.
steps.Step 6: Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
steps.Step 7: Garnish with chopped fresh cilantro.

2794.title: Lemony Banana Crumb Muffins
2794.description: Light, lemony muffins with a crunchy crumble topping. This recipe yields a small batch (6 to 8) of regular-sized muffins, or 12 to 15 large-capped mini muffins.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) and grease a 12-cup mini muffin pan.
steps.Step 2: Combine brown sugar, flour, coconut, and lemon zest in a bowl for crumb topping. Rub in butter until the mixture is coarse and crumbly.
steps.Step 3: Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice to milk and let sit until curdled, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Cream white sugar and butter in a medium bowl. Mix banana and egg together in another bowl and add lemon zest, remaining lemon juice, and vanilla extract. Add the banana mixture to the creamed butter and sugar and stir well. Add the curdled milk and stir lightly into the mixture.
steps.Step 5: Combine self-rising flour, all-purpose flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, and cinnamon in a large bowl. Pour in the banana mixture and stir until just combined.
steps.Step 6: Drop by heaping spoonfuls into the prepared muffin pan, filling about 1/8 inch higher than the cups, ensuring nice, top-heavy muffins. Sprinkle with the crumb topping, lightly pressing it into the batter so it doesn't fall off and melt during cooking.
steps.Step 7: Bake in the preheated oven until golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool slightly in the pan before removing to a wire rack.

2838.title: Instant Pot Turkey Bolognese
2838.description: A hearty Bolognese sauce made with turkey instead of beef, perfect for picky eaters as it can hide some veggies.  Serve with freshly shaved Parmesan cheese.

steps.Step 1: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil; cook rotini at a boil until tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Meanwhile, turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot) and select Saute function. Allow pot to get hot, then add turkey, shallot, garlic granules, and Italian seasoning. Cook, breaking up turkey until crumbly and browned, about 5 minutes. Cancel Saute mode. Level out turkey mixture. Spread the carrots and zucchini over the top.
steps.Step 3: Mix marinara sauce and milk together. Pour over the vegetables. Place cream cheese on top. Do not stir. Close and lock the lid. Select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 5 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.
steps.Step 4: Drain pasta. Release pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 5 minutes. Unlock and remove the lid. Add drained pasta and stir to combine.

2848.title: Pumpkin Apple Muffins
2848.description: These muffins are a delicious fall treat, combining the flavors of pumpkin and apple with whole wheat flour for a wholesome twist. They are moist and flavorful, perfect for breakfast, brunch, or an afternoon snack.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F.
steps.Step 2: Combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda, salt and baking powder in a medium bowl. Whisk together.
steps.Step 3: Whisk together pumpkin, apple, oil, egg and vanilla in a large bowl.
steps.Step 4: Add dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
steps.Step 5: Stir in cranberries and flax seed.
steps.Step 6: Portion into greased muffin cups or use paper liners. Sprinkle with walnuts.
steps.Step 7: Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
steps.Step 8: Cool in pan on wire rack 5 minutes. Remove from pan.

2866.title: Harvest Pumpkin Cupcakes
2866.description: Rich and spicy pumpkin cupcakes with orange cream cheese frosting.

ingredients.name: Spice Islands® 100% Pure Bourbon Vanilla Extract

steps.Step 1: Blend the eggs, oil, sugar, and pumpkin in a large mixing bowl; set aside.
steps.Step 2: Stir together dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
steps.Step 3: Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture and beat until well blended.
steps.Step 4: POUR into lined muffin tins. Fill about 2/3 full.
steps.Step 5: Bake in preheated 350 degrees oven for 30 minutes or until center springs back when touched.
steps.Step 6: Cool 30 minutes.
steps.Step 7: Spread with frosting.
steps.Step 8: Beat cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
steps.Step 9: Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.

2890.title: Huge Cinnamon Rolls
2890.description: Big, soft, and chewy cinnamon rolls with a perfect balance of sticky sweetness. Wonderful when served warm.

steps.Step 1: Gently mix 1/4 cup warm water, 1 tablespoon sugar, and yeast for dough in a small bowl. Let sit to proof until yeast is frothy and nearly doubled in volume, about 10 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Meanwhile, heat milk in a small saucepan over medium-low heat until it bubbles, about 3 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in margarine until melted.
steps.Step 3: Combine 2 1/4 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt, and yeast mixture in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the dough hook; mix well. Add 1/4 cup water, egg, and the warm milk-margarine mixture; mix until combined. Add the remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition. You may not need all the flour; ideally the dough will remain a bit sticky but should be manageable with floured hands.
steps.Step 4: Carefully knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth, about 5 minutes. Continue to flour your hands so the dough doesn't stick to them. Cover the dough with a damp cloth and let rest for 10 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Meanwhile, mix brown sugar, margarine, raisins, pecans, and cinnamon for filling together in a small bowl. Sprinkle a thin amount of filling on the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish, then spray with cooking spray.
steps.Step 6: Roll the dough into a 1/4-inch thick rectangle measuring 9x12 inches. Cut into 6 equal strips. Spread each strip with a thin, even layer of filling (too much may be too sweet) and roll up. Transfer to the baking dish. Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 30 minutes.
steps.Step 7: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).
steps.Step 8: Bake rolls in the preheated oven until browned, about 20 minutes. Remove from the pan to cool.
steps.Step 9: Mix frosting, brown sugar, and cinnamon for icing together in a bowl. Pour in melted margarine slowly and mix to a smooth and thick consistency that is liquid enough to pour. Pour a spoonful of icing over warm rolls.

2892.title: Chewy Pumpkin Cookies
2892.description: These chewy pumpkin cookies are a fall favorite, with a soft texture and a hint of pumpkin spice. They're perfect for fall gatherings or a cozy evening in.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
steps.Step 2: Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt in a bowl.
steps.Step 3: Cream butter in a large bowl with an electric mixer. Gradually add brown and white sugars; beat until light and fluffy. Mix in egg and vanilla extract until well combined.
steps.Step 4: Add flour mixture in 3 batches, alternating with pumpkin, mixing well after each addition. Stir in chocolate chips.
steps.Step 5: Drop medium spoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto the prepared baking sheets and spread into pumpkin shapes.
steps.Step 6: Bake in the preheated oven until cookies are slightly firm and lightly browned, 20 to 25 minutes; do not overbake.
steps.Step 7: Cool on the baking sheet briefly before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

2902.title: Overnight Cinnamon Rolls
2902.description: A delicious cinnamon roll recipe that rises in the refrigerator overnight. The recipe yields 12 rolls and includes a cream cheese frosting.

steps.Step 1: Combine water and yeast; let sit for 5 minutes until yeast has dissolved.
steps.Step 2: Mix sugar, shortening, salt, and yeast mixture together in a large bowl. Stir in egg. Mix in 1/2 of the flour, then remaining flour until a dough forms. Transfer dough to a well-greased bowl and cover. Place in the refrigerator to rise, 8 hours to overnight.
steps.Step 3: Remove dough from the refrigerator. Roll out on a lightly floured board. Spread softened butter over the surface of the dough, leaving a 1-inch strip along the long edge of the rectangle furthest away from you completely dry.
steps.Step 4: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon, and cloves together in a bowl. Sprinkle all over the dough except the 1-inch border. Roll dough up toward the border, then cut into 1-inch thick rolls.
steps.Step 5: Place in a greased pan and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
steps.Step 6: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).
steps.Step 7: Bake rolls in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Spread cream cheese frosting on top of hot rolls.

2939.title: Lemon Poppy Seed Scones
2939.description: These scones are a simple but potentially tricky recipe.  The dough initially has a rough texture, but proper handling results in tender scones. A strawberry glaze adds a fruity touch, making them perfect for special occasions.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Place self-rising flour in a large bowl. Cut in butter using a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add poppy seeds, sugar, and lemon zest; mix to combine.
steps.Step 3: Make a well in the center and pour in egg, lemon juice, and milk. Mix with a fork until dough starts to come together. Scoop up with one hand until a shaggy dough forms.
steps.Step 4: Pour dough out onto your work surface. Use your hands and a bench scraper to gather and press dough into a neat rectangle about 1- to 1-1/2-inches tall. Cut into 4 squares and then diagonally into 8 triangles.
steps.Step 5: Space scones evenly onto a silicone-lined baking sheet.
steps.Step 6: Bake in the preheated oven until bottoms are golden brown, about 25 minutes.
steps.Step 7: Let cool in pan for 5 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely, about 30 minutes.
steps.Step 8: Mash strawberries finely to resemble a puree. Whisk in powdered sugar in batches to make a thick, spreadable glaze.
steps.Step 9: Spread glaze over the cooled scones. Let scones cool on the rack until glaze hardens, about 20 minutes.

3035.title: Bourbon Pepper Pan Sauce
3035.description: A rich, sweet, and peppery pan sauce perfect for steaks, pork chops, or grilled chicken.  The recipe features a simple technique for creating a flavorful sauce using bourbon, chicken broth, and heavy cream.

steps.Step 1: Season both sides of the steaks generously with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 2: Melt duck fat in a steel pan over medium-high heat. Add steaks; cook until firm and reddish-pink in the center for medium-rare, about 5 minutes per side. Sear the edges until browned, about 30 seconds each. Transfer steaks to a plate; let rest while you make the sauce. Turn off the heat.
steps.Step 3: Stir garlic into the same pan using a spoon. Add 1 teaspoon butter; let melt. Pour in bourbon. Heat until reduced to a sticky glaze, about 15 seconds. Add chicken stock. Bring to a boil over high heat while scraping up the browned bits at the bottom to deglaze. Cook until reduced by half, about 2 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Add heavy cream; season with salt and cayenne pepper. Boil until thickened, 2 to 3 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Turn off heat and add remaining 2 teaspoons butter; swirl until melted, about 30 seconds more. Spoon sauce warm onto serving plates. Place steaks on top.

3039.title: Stuffed Alfredo Baked Potatoes
3039.description: Delicious stuffed baked potatoes are perfect for a quick and easy weeknight meal.  A creamy spinach-mushroom Alfredo sauce is poured into and over the potatoes, making a satisfying and flavorful side dish.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Place rack in the center of the oven.
steps.Step 2: Arrange potatoes on a baking sheet. Bake until easily pierced with a fork, 50 minutes to an hour.
steps.Step 3: Heat butter and olive oil in skillet over medium heat. Saute mushrooms until they begin to soften and brown. Add spinach; cook and stir until spinach is wilted, 3 to 4 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Stir in the Classico® Fresh Creamy Alfredo Sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook about 5 minutes to slightly thicken the sauce.
steps.Step 5: Cut a slit in the potatoes and squeeze the sides to loosen the flesh. To serve, pour some of the creamy spinach-mushroom sauce into and over the potato. Sprinkle with chopped tomatoes.

3042.title: Chocolate Peanut Butter Blossom Cookies
3042.description: These cookies offer a decadent twist on traditional peanut butter blossoms, featuring a chocolate-peanut butter dough topped with dark chocolate kisses.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line two cookie sheets with Reynolds® Parchment Paper.
steps.Step 2: Beat the shortening and peanut butter in a large bowl with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add the brown sugar, baking powder, and baking soda. Beat until combined, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally. Beat in the egg, milk, and vanilla until combined. Beat in as much of the flour and cocoa powder as you can with the mixer, using a wooden spoon at the end if necessary.
steps.Step 3: Place the granulated sugar in a small bowl. Shape the dough into 1-inch balls. Roll the balls in sugar to coat. Place the balls 2 inches apart on the prepared cookie sheets.
steps.Step 4: Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are firm. Immediately press a dark chocolate candy into the center of each cookie. Slide the parchment with the cookies on it to a wire rack; cool completely.

3069.title: Fresh Strawberry Marble Cake
3069.description: A delightful strawberry marble cake with a creamy cream cheese frosting.  Perfect for birthdays or any special occasion.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line the bottoms of three 8-inch cake pans with parchment paper; grease and flour the sides.
steps.Step 2: Puree whole strawberries in the bowl of a food processor or electric blender and set aside.
steps.Step 3: Mix flour, baking soda, and salt together in a bowl.
steps.Step 4: Beat sugar and butter together in a large bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla extract. Add flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
steps.Step 5: Beat egg whites in another large bowl with an electric mixer on high speed until peaks form. Gently stir into the batter.
steps.Step 6: Pour 1/2 of the batter in a medium bowl and set aside. Add pureed strawberries and food coloring to the remaining batter and mix well.
steps.Step 7: Pour batters evenly into the prepared cake pans, alternating between red and white batter in each pan.
steps.Step 8: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of each layer comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Immediately run a spatula between the cakes and the sides of the pans. Let cool for 15 minutes; remove cakes from the pans. Remove paper. Cool completely on wire racks.
steps.Step 9: While cakes are cooling, mix confectioners' sugar, cream cheese, butter, milk, strawberry extract, vanilla extract, and food coloring together in a bowl. Let sit for 15 to 30 minutes.
steps.Step 10: Frost the bottom cooled cake layer and add 1/2 of the sliced strawberries evenly. Repeat for second layer. Add the top layer. Frost the top and sides, covering any trace of strawberries in the layers.

3080.title: Strawberry Buttermilk Crumb Cake
3080.description: This cake features a combination of tender crumb and sweet strawberries, baked in a single bowl without a mixer.  The prep time is minimal, while the bake time may be somewhat longer.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Line a 9-inch square cake pan with parchment paper.
steps.Step 2: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and nutmeg in a large bowl.
steps.Step 3: Cut in butter until mixture resembles wet sand. Measure out 1 cup of the crumb mixture to use for the topping, and set aside.
steps.Step 4: Add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla to the dry ingredients. Mix until there are no dry clumps of flour remaining.
steps.Step 5: Fold in strawberries.
steps.Step 6: Pour batter into the prepared pan and smooth into an even layer.
steps.Step 7: Sprinkle 1 cup reserved crumb mixture evenly over the top.
steps.Step 8: Place pan into the preheated oven and bake until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out with a few moist crumbs, 60 to 65 minutes.
steps.Step 9: Allow cake to cool completely in pan before carefully lifting out of pan using the parchment overhang. Cut and serve.

3082.title: Strawberry Spoon Cake
3082.description: This strawberry spoon cake is a delightful mix of spoonbread, pudding cake, and biscuit, topped with fresh strawberries for a simple yet delicious home-style dessert.  It's best enjoyed warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream, ensuring a soft, slightly underbaked center.

steps.Step 1: Combine strawberries, 2 tablespoons sugar, and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Toss to combine and allow to sit for about 10 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Place butter into a 10-inch cast iron skillet. Place skillet into the oven and heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees). Allow the butter to melt as the oven preheats.
steps.Step 3: Meanwhile, whisk together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl until thoroughly combined.
steps.Step 4: Carefully remove the skillet from the oven; swirl to spread butter evenly. Pour remaining melted butter into the flour mixture. Set the skillet aside to cool slightly. Add buttermilk and vanilla to the flour and butter mixture. Stir just until no dry clumps of flour remain. Pour batter back into the skillet, and spread into an even layer. Spoon strawberries and their juices over the top.
steps.Step 5: Place skillet back into the oven, and bake until center of the cake is just barely set, 32 to 37 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes before serving. Serve warm.

3085.title: Guava Banana Smoothie
3085.description: This is a delicious recipe for eating on the go.

steps.Step 1: Combine guava juice, milk, banana, and ice cubes in a blender.
steps.Step 2: Blend on high until well combined.

3103.title: Coffee Barbecue Sauce
3103.description: This barbecue sauce combines the flavors of coffee and other ingredients for a unique taste. It's suitable for grilled chicken, beef, or pork, and it keeps well in the refrigerator for up to three months.
3103.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.
3103.dietary_fiber: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Combine ketchup, coffee, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, oil, and cayenne in a medium nonreactive saucepan over medium heat.
steps.Step 2: Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
steps.Step 3: Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Remove from the heat and cool.
steps.Step 5: Transfer to a tightly covered container and store in the refrigerator.

3133.title: Homemade Italian Sausage
3133.description: A flavorful homemade Italian sausage recipe, inspired by a family tradition.  The recipe allows for a dry-aging process for enhanced flavor and texture.

steps.Step 1: Cut pork shoulder into cubes. Place in a bowl and refrigerate while preparing the other ingredients.
steps.Step 2: Grind garlic with a pinch of salt in a mortar to make a paste. Add fennel, anise, and black pepper. Bruise spices lightly with a pestle to release the flavors. Add red pepper flakes, cayenne pepper, oregano, marjoram, coriander, mustard, allspice, sugar, and a splash of water. Stir to combine.
steps.Step 3: Add the spice paste to the pork cubes. Mix thoroughly by hand. Add the remaining salt. Cover and refrigerate until flavors meld, 8 hours to overnight.
steps.Step 4: Process the cold pork through a meat grinder on the slowest speed.
steps.Step 5: Push a casing onto the stuffing tube of your meat grinder. Feed the sausage meat through the filling tray. Run the meat through the casing on the slowest speed until all the casing is used up. Tie casing at the end into a knot. Pinch and twist the meat to create links if desired.
steps.Step 6: Place sausage onto a wire rack set over a sheet pan. Refrigerate uncovered for 24 hours.
steps.Step 7: Preheat a charcoal grill for medium heat. Separate the links and grill them until browned, about 5 minutes per side.

3145.title: Penang Pork Satay
3145.description: This recipe features a flavorful pork satay marinade, perfect for grilling or broiling.  The satay is served over rice with peanut sauce and a cucumber salad, delivering an explosive combination of flavors.

steps.Step 1: Place fresh turmeric and powdered turmeric in a food processor. Add ginger, shallot, garlic, brown sugar, ancho chili powder, coriander, chipotle, cayenne, rice vinegar, soy sauce, fish sauce, tamarind paste, and cilantro. Blend into a fine paste.
steps.Step 2: Cut pork into 1 1/2-inch cubes, trimming off fat as needed. Place pork in a bowl; season with salt. Pour in the marinade. Mix and massage pork with your hands until completely coated. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 to 18 hours.
steps.Step 3: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate. Thread pork through skewers so the pieces are touching but not squished together. Reserve leftover marinade.
steps.Step 4: Grill skewers, brushing on reserved marinade, until pork just starts to firm up but is still slightly pink in the center, about 10 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read 145 degrees F (63 degrees C). Serve immediately.

3146.title: Seafood Sausage
3146.description: A flavorful and unique sausage made from a blend of seafood, including sole, salmon, and shrimp, bound together with breadcrumbs, eggs, and herbs. The recipe includes a tangy sauce to complement the sausage.

steps.Step 1: Melt 2 teaspoons butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Saute shallots until soft and sweetened, about 5 minutes. Let cool to room temperature.
steps.Step 2: Combine sole, salmon, and shrimp in a food processor. Add bread crumbs. Pour in egg whites and whole egg. Season with kosher salt and cayenne pepper. Add the cooled shallots and parsley.
steps.Step 3: Cover processor and pulse on and off, starting with short pulses and transitioning to longer ones, until mixture is well blended and clumps together at the blade. Transfer mixture to a bowl, wrap in plastic wrap, and chill in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
steps.Step 4: Transfer 1/4 of the sausage mixture onto a piece of plastic wrap. Shape into a log with dampened fingertips. Roll in the plastic, twisting the ends to seal. Lay the log onto a piece of aluminum foil and roll it up. Twist the ends in opposite directions, but not too tightly. Fold the ends back. Repeat with the remaining sausage mixture.
steps.Step 5: Bring a pot of water to a simmer. Add the sausages and submerge them with a plate. Cover pot and simmer on low for 20 minutes.
steps.Step 6: Transfer sausages into a bowl of cold water to stop the cooking process. Let cool for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from the water and refrigerate until ready to serve.
steps.Step 7: Peel foil off of the sausages over a piece of paper towel. Snip off 1 end of the plastic wrap and squeeze the sausage out through the opening. Trim off any unsightly chunks.
steps.Step 8: Melt remaining butter in a pan over medium heat. Cook sausages in the hot butter, turning until browned all over, 5 to 6 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low and cover. Cook until an instant-read thermometer inserted into the sausages reads 140 degrees F (60 degrees C), 5 to 6 minutes more. Repeat with remaining sausages.
steps.Step 9: Pour water and lemon juice into the same pan and bring to a boil. Cook until reduced by 1/2, about 3 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add cold butter and parsley. Swirl pan until butter is melted; season with salt and swirl once more. Spoon sauce over the sausages.

3194.title: Goan Chicken Masala Curry
3194.description: An Indian red masala curry recipe from Goa.  It involves making your own masala paste but it's worth it! A great family meal with enough for leftovers.

steps.Step 1: Combine red chile peppers, cumin seeds, coriander seeds, cinnamon stick, ginger, garlic, peppercorns, and cloves in a mortar and pestle or a food processor; grind or process into a paste (masala paste).
steps.Step 2: Heat oil in a large pot. Add onion and until golden brown. Stir in masala paste and cook for 2 minutes. Add pieces of chicken; mix well and pour in enough cold water to cover the chicken. Bring to a boil.
steps.Step 3: Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 30 minutes. Season to taste with tamarind juice and salt. Stir well and cook for additional 5 minutes. Garnish with fresh cilantro.

3197.title: Thai Red Curry Chicken Bake
3197.description: This baked chicken dish is an easy take on Thai red curry, made in the oven. Serve with steamed rice.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Season chicken thighs with salt and pepper and place in a roasting pan.
steps.Step 2: Mix coconut milk, curry paste, and brown sugar in a bowl until well blended. Pour over chicken. Place onions on top of chicken and cover with aluminum foil.
steps.Step 3: Bake in the preheated oven until chicken is no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, 45 minutes to 1 hour. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 180 degrees F (82 degrees C).

3209.title: Pumpkin Thai Curry Pot Pie
3209.description: A fall-inspired, hearty pumpkin Thai curry chicken pot pie offering a new twist on a comforting dish.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Heat oil in a pot over medium-low heat. Season chicken with salt and pepper and add to hot oil. Stir in onion, 2 tablespoons curry paste, garlic, harissa, onion salt, and garlic powder; cook until onion is soft and chicken is browned, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Stir in enough cornstarch to thicken. Pour in 1 can of coconut milk. Add remaining curry paste and pumpkin. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook for 10 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Uncover and add peas, beans, and chile pepper. Stir in brown sugar, lime juice, fish sauce, and sea salt. Pour in remaining can of coconut milk.
steps.Step 5: Transfer the mixture into a 2-quart baking dish or oven-safe bowl. Arrange biscuits on top of the filling. Brush tops with beaten egg.
steps.Step 6: Bake in the preheated oven until biscuits are golden brown, about 20 minutes.

3211.title: Thai Yellow Curry Chicken
3211.description: A mildly spicy and absolutely splendiferous curry. Deep rich flavors from the chicken and coconut. The spice of the yellow curry pairs perfectly with the sweetness of the coconut milk. Tastes like Thailand. Garnish with your preferred aromatic.

steps.Step 1: Gently melt butter in a large skillet over low heat. Add curry paste; cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in coconut milk and bring to a simmer.
steps.Step 2: Heat olive oil in a separate skillet over medium heat; stir in onion and garlic. Saute until onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes. Add chicken and chicken base and cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Transfer chicken mixture into the coconut-curry sauce. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Meanwhile, combine water and rice in a saucepan. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until all water has been absorbed, about 9 minutes. Turn off the heat and let rice sit, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes. Uncover and fluff with a fork.
steps.Step 5: Serve chicken curry over rice. Garnish with cashews just before serving.

3254.title: Instant Pot Vegetarian Pozole
3254.description: A vegetarian version of the traditional Mexican pozole, made quickly and easily in an Instant Pot.  Perfect for any day of the week, and customizable with your favorite toppings.

steps.Step 1: Turn on a multi-functional pressure cooker and select Saute function. Add olive oil, onion, and guajillo chiles. Cook for 3 minutes. Add garlic, cumin, and oregano; cook for 2 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Cancel Saute function. Pour broth, pinto beans, hominy, and enchilada sauce into the pot. Stir to combine. Close and lock the lid. Select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 20 minutes. Allow 20 minutes for pressure to build.
steps.Step 3: Release pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 5 minutes. Unlock and remove the lid. Discard the guajillo chiles. Stir in cilantro and lime juice.

3287.title: Banana Coconut Pecan Muffins
3287.description: These banana muffins with pecans and coconut are fantastic for breakfast, served alongside a lovely fruit assortment and coffee.

ingredients.name: So Delicious® Dairy Free Original Coconut Milk

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees and line muffin pans with muffin/cupcake liners. You can also lightly spray the pan if you don't have liners.
steps.Step 2: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Stir and set aside.
steps.Step 3: In a larger bowl, mix sugar and oil together then add mashed bananas. Note: I didn't want to dirty another bowl so I peeled each banana and squished them individually with my clean hands right into the bowl. This 'technique' makes for a chunkier banana consistency, which I like for a breakfast muffin. If you do not like that, mash the bananas in a separate bowl then add to the sugar/oil mixture.
steps.Step 4: To your wet mix also add coconut milk and vanilla, stirring until everything is thoroughly combined.
steps.Step 5: Add flour mixture to wet mixture and stir lightly, then add pecans and coconut. Stir until everything is just combined. Note: the batter will be fairly thick.
steps.Step 6: Spoon batter into muffin tins about 3/4 full.
steps.Step 7: Bake for 20-25 minutes until muffins are golden brown on top.

3306.title: Vegan Southern Greens
3306.description: A spicy, savory, vegan dish with loads of fresh veggies and black-eyed peas. So delicious! Serve over rice as an entree or by itself as a side dish. Best enjoyed with a big glass of sweet tea.

steps.Step 1: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat; add garlic and cook until it begins to brown, 1 to 2 minutes. Add kale and chard, a handful at a time; continue to cook, stirring often, until greens brighten, about 3 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Add black-eyed peas, okra, and vegetable broth; stir until incorporated with greens. Add cumin, chili powder, brown sugar, cayenne, and salt; bring to a boil.
steps.Step 3: Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Serve topped with sliced tomatoes and a squeeze of lemon juice.

3375.title: Classic Cinnamon Rolls
3375.description: These classic cinnamon rolls are a delicious treat, perfect for a special occasion or a comforting everyday indulgence. The recipe combines a soft, fluffy dough with a sweet cinnamon filling and a creamy icing, resulting in a delightful experience.

ingredients.name: Spice Islands® 100% Pure Bourbon Vanilla Extract

steps.Step 1: Combine potatoes, potato water, butter, sugar, salt and hot water in large mixing bowl. Stir until butter melts; set aside and let cool.
steps.Step 2: Combine yeast and ½ cup warm water in small bowl. Let rest 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Add eggs, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture to potato mixture. Beat until well mixed. Continue adding flour, 1 cup at a time until soft dough forms.
steps.Step 4: Knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic (about 4 to 6 minutes), OR knead with electric mixer using dough hook.
steps.Step 5: Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to coat. Cover.
steps.Step 6: Let rise in a warm, draft free area about 1 hour, until doubled in size. Punch dough down; divide in half.
steps.Step 7: Roll one portion of dough on a lightly floured surface to a 12 x 18-inch rectangle. Spread with half the butter. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle half of the mixture over surface. Roll up tightly lengthwise, sealing edges. Cut into 12 slices. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
steps.Step 8: Repeat with remaining dough. Cover.
steps.Step 9: Let rise 30 to 45 minutes until nearly doubled.
steps.Step 10: Bake in preheated 350 degrees F oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
steps.Step 11: Cool for 15 minutes. Combine icing ingredients and drizzle over rolls.

3379.title: Banana Bread Pancakes
3379.description: These pancakes are inspired by banana bread, offering a unique flavor and texture that combines the deliciousness of banana bread with the classic pancake experience.  Topped with butter, banana slices, and warm maple syrup, they make a delightful breakfast treat.

steps.Step 1: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda in a small bowl with a whisk. Reserve until needed.
steps.Step 2: Place banana in a mixing bowl and mash into a smooth paste with a potato masher. Add egg and sugar and whisk thoroughly until sugar is dissolved and mixture is smooth and creamy, about 2 minutes. Add milk, vanilla extract, 1/4 cup melted butter, walnuts, and flour mixture. Whisk until just combined.
steps.Step 3: Let batter rest for 10 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large, nonstick pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, transfer in about 1/3 cup of the batter per pancake. Reduce heat to medium and cook until edges start to look dry and small air bubbles pop up through the surface, about 3 minutes. Flip and cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes more. Serve immediately.

3384.title: Fruity Mini Pancake Skewers
3384.description: These mini pancake skewers are a fun and delicious finger food, perfect for breakfast, brunch, snacks, or game-day buffets. The colorful combination of pancakes, fruit, and cream cheese is sure to please kids and adults alike.

steps.Step 1: Whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt in a bowl.
steps.Step 2: Whisk milk, egg, butter, and amaretto extract together in a second bowl.
steps.Step 3: Pour wet ingredients into the flour mixture, and mix until batter is well combined and smooth.
steps.Step 4: Heat a large nonstick skillet or griddle over medium heat.
steps.Step 5: Drop teaspoonfuls of batter onto the hot skillet to form 1-inch diameter pancakes.
steps.Step 6: Cook for about 1 to 2 minutes, flip, and continue cooking until golden brown, about 1 more minute.
steps.Step 7: Transfer cooked pancakes to a plate and repeat with remaining batter.
steps.Step 8: Stack ingredients on a work surface as follows: pancake, banana, pancake spread with cream cheese, pancake, strawberry, and pancake. (Each skewer will use 4 pancakes).
steps.Step 9: Insert a skewer through the center of the stack and repeat to make remaining skewers.
steps.Step 10: Dust with confectioners sugar, and serve.

3393.title: French Toast Mini Dutch Babies
3393.description: These mini custard-like cups have all the flavor of French toast, but are most similar to Dutch baby pancakes in texture. Like Dutch babies, they puff dramatically while baking and deflate just as dramatically when out of the oven. I like to serve them topped with a bit of yogurt and fresh berries.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Combine milk, flour, eggs, maple syrup, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt in a blender. Blend until batter is smooth and free of lumps, 1 to 2 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Cut butter into 12 equal pieces; place 1 piece in each cup of a 12-cup standard muffin pan. Place pan into the oven to melt butter, about 1 minute. Remove from the oven and divide pancake batter evenly between the cups.
steps.Step 4: Place muffin pan on a baking sheet to catch spills, and place in the preheated oven. Bake until pancakes are puffed and browned on the edges, 10 to 15 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Remove from the oven and cool in the muffin pan for 2 minutes. Run a knife around the edges and bottoms to loosen and serve immediately.

3395.title: Buttery Strawberry Shmear
3395.description: This shmear is delicious on bagels, toast, crackers, as a dip, or by the spoonful! Adjust sweetener accordingly to the sweetness of your strawberries.

steps.Step 1: Place strawberries in a blender and blend until pureed. Measure out 3 tablespoons strawberry puree and set aside. Save the rest, if any, for another use.
steps.Step 2: Combine butter, Neufchatel cheese, and sweetener in a blender and blend until smooth. Add strawberry puree and blend until fully incorporated.

3402.title: Banana Berry Bread
3402.description: This banana bread is made moist by the berries, with no butter or oil.  A very berry bread (or muffin) recipe.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease 2 loaf pans.
steps.Step 2: Pour sugar and lightly beaten eggs into a large bowl and mix well. Add bananas, vanilla extract, and lemon juice. Stir in strawberries. Fold in blueberries.
steps.Step 3: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder, and nutmeg in a medium bowl. Mix with a fork. Add to wet ingredients, slowly folding in until moist. Pour into the prepared loaf pans.
steps.Step 4: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool for 20 minutes in the pans and then turn out onto a cooling rack for 30 minutes before eating.

3419.title: Radish Shmear
3419.description: A flavorful radish spread, perfect as a bagel topping or a dip for vegetables. It combines cream cheese, butter, and radishes for a tangy and crunchy flavor.

steps.Step 1: Combine cream cheese, butter, celery salt, Worcestershire, and paprika together in a bowl; mix until smooth.
steps.Step 2: Stir in radishes and green onions.
steps.Step 3: Chill until flavors have blended, about 3 hours.

3424.title: Coconut Oil Pie Crust
3424.description: This is a butter/shortening-free pie crust. It is a bit healthier and just as tasty, flaky and buttery tasting. This makes 2 crusts and works for both sweet or savory pies. Just add 1 teaspoon sugar if you're making a sweet pie. Make sure to use refined coconut oil to hide the coconut taste. Unless of course you will use this for a coconut pie!

steps.Step 1: Combine flour, coconut oil, and salt in a food processor and pulse until combined.
steps.Step 2: Add 5 tablespoons ice cold water and pulse. With the food processor running at low speed, add 1 additional tablespoon of water at a time until a dough forms.
steps.Step 3: Using your hands, pat dough to shape into a ball. Cut in half for 2 pie crusts.
steps.Step 4: Flour a work surface and rolling pin and roll out dough.
steps.Step 5: Bake as directed for any pie recipe you are following.

3460.title: Delicious Salmon
3460.description: This easy salmon recipe is broiled to perfection and served with rice and broccoli. The salmon is marinated in a simple soy sauce, olive oil, brown sugar, lemon pepper, and garlic mixture for a flavorful dish.

steps.Step 1: Whisk together the soy sauce, olive oil, brown sugar, lemon pepper, and garlic in a shallow dish; lay the salmon fillets into the mixture with the skin side facing up.
steps.Step 2: Allow to marinate in the refrigerator 4 to 8 hours or overnight.
steps.Step 3: Preheat the oven's broiler and set the oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source.
steps.Step 4: Remove salmon from the marinade and arrange on a baking sheet. Discard the marinade.
steps.Step 5: Cook the salmon under the broiler until lightly browned and the flesh flakes easily with a fork, 7 to 10 minutes.
steps.Step 6: Allow the salmon to rest 5 minutes before slicing and serving.

3464.title: Balsamic Vinaigrette
3464.description: A tangy vinaigrette, perfect for mixed greens, tomato, onion, and cucumber salads. Also good for steamed vegetables or stir-fries, although used sparingly.

steps.Step 1: Whisk together olive oil, white balsamic vinegar, garlic, and mustard powder in a small bowl.
steps.Step 2: Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
steps.Step 3: Stir in minced fresh herbs, if desired.

3480.title: Clean Green Vinaigrette
3480.description: This fresh vinaigrette is an easy way to add some green to your meals, using fresh dill and chives.

steps.Step 1: Place oil, vinegar, dill, chives, shallot, sugar, salt, and pepper in a screw-top jar.
steps.Step 2: Cover and shake well to combine.

3537.title: Beef Tenderloin With Roasted Shallots
3537.description: A rich and flavorful beef tenderloin dish featuring a decadent shallot sauce. The recipe is suitable for gatherings and doubles well for larger parties.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). In 9 inch pie pan, toss shallots with oil to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Roast until shallots are deep brown and very tender, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
steps.Step 2: In a large saucepan, combine beef broth and port. Bring to a boil. Cook over high heat until the volume is reduced by half, about 30 minutes. Whisk in tomato paste. Set aside.
steps.Step 3: Pat beef dry; sprinkle with thyme, salt and pepper. In a large roasting pan, set over medium heat on the stove top, saute bacon until golden. Using a slotted spoon, transfer bacon to paper towels. Add beef to pan; brown on all sides over medium high heat, about 7 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Transfer pan to oven. Roast beef until meat thermometer inserted into center registers 125 degrees F (50 degrees C) for medium rare, about 25 minutes. Transfer beef to platter. Tent loosely with foil.
steps.Step 5: Spoon fat off top of pan drippings in roasting pan. Place pan over high heat on stove top. Add broth mixture, and bring to boil; stir to scrape up any browned bits. Transfer to a medium saucepan, and bring to simmer. Mix 1 1/2 tablespoon butter and flour in small bowl to form smooth paste; whisk into broth mixture, and simmer until sauce thickens. Whisk in remaining butter. Stir in roasted shallots and reserved bacon. Season with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 6: Cut beef into 1/2 inch thick slices. Spoon some sauce over, and garnish with watercress.

3550.title: Easy Orange Ricotta Cake
3550.description: An easy recipe using a cake mix. The added ricotta cheese, orange juice, and orange zest kicks the flavors up a notch.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a fluted tube pan (such as Bundt®).
steps.Step 2: Prepare cake: combine cake mix, eggs, ricotta cheese, oil, orange juice, orange zest, and orange extract in a large bowl. Mix until batter is well combined.
steps.Step 3: Pour batter into prepared pan.
steps.Step 4: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack and let cool in the pan for 15 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Carefully invert onto a serving platter and let cool completely, about 1 hour.
steps.Step 6: Prepare glaze: mix powdered sugar, orange juice, and orange zest together in a small bowl.
steps.Step 7: Drizzle glaze over the cooled cake.

3559.title: Orange Drizzle Cake
3559.description: A simple yet delicious orange cake, easily adaptable by substituting citrus fruits. This moist cake is not overly sweet and will disappear quickly.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9-inch cake pan well using butter and flour.
steps.Step 2: Combine flour, eggs, sugar, butter, orange juice, orange zest, and baking powder in a bowl. Mix with an electric hand mixer or stand mixer until batter comes together and is pale in color. Pour into the prepared pan.
steps.Step 3: Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from the oven and let cool in the pan for 5 minutes. Carefully remove from the pan and place on a cooling rack with a tray underneath.
steps.Step 4: While cake cools, combine sugar and orange juice for drizzle in a small bowl. Pour over the still-warm cake. Let cool completely before slicing.

3567.title: Negroni Bars
3567.description: These colorful cookie bars are inspired by a negroni cocktail. If not serving immediately, cover pan and keep refrigerated.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Grease and line a 9x13-inch baking pan.
steps.Step 2: Combine crushed pretzels, brown sugar, and milk powder in a medium mixing bowl. Add butter to the bowl and toss to combine. Press the pretzel mixture into the bottom of the prepared pan.
steps.Step 3: Bake in the preheated oven until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack to cool.
steps.Step 4: Increase oven temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 5: Whisk sugar, eggs, flour, and grapefruit zest together in a large bowl. Whisk in orange juice, grapefruit juice, orange aperitif, gin, and vermouth. Pour over the pretzel crust.
steps.Step 6: Bake in the preheated oven until filling is set, 30 to 35 minutes. Cover with foil if filling starts browning too quickly.
steps.Step 7: Cool completely on a wire rack, 20 to 30 minutes. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
steps.Step 8: Pulse freeze-dried strawberries in a food processor until finely ground. Use a fine-mesh strainer to dust strawberry powder over the filling.
steps.Step 9: Cut into 24 bars and serve.

3603.title: Copycat Dipping Sauce
3603.description: A simple recipe for a copycat dipping sauce, similar to Chick-fil-A's dipping sauce, using just four common ingredients.

steps.Step 1: Mix mayonnaise, yellow mustard, barbecue sauce, and honey together in a small bowl.

3686.title: Pineapple Sorbet
3686.description: Sweet and tangy pineapple sorbet, perfect for summer. The mint adds a refreshing touch to the pineapple flavor.
3686.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Place pineapple, pineapple juice, sugar, lime juice, vodka, and mint in a food processor and process until smooth.
steps.Step 2: Pour mixture into an ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions, about 20 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Transfer to an airtight container; put in the freezer for at least 6 hours before serving so it can firm up.

3708.title: Tortilla Chorizo Scramble
3708.description: This chilaquiles-inspired tortilla chorizo scramble is a great way to dress up high-fiber, whole wheat tortillas.

steps.Step 1: Beat eggs in a small bowl. Set aside.
steps.Step 2: Combine tortilla slices and chorizo in a skillet over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until tortillas are crisped, 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Place cheese slices on top of chorizo and tortillas; pour in eggs. Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring, until eggs are cooked through, 3 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste; garnish with chives.

3713.title: Romano Bean Salad
3713.description: A simple yet elegant side dish/salad made with fresh romano or green beans, dressed with a mixture of olive oil, white wine vinegar, garlic, and mint.  Best enjoyed after marinating overnight for a pickled bean-like flavor.
3713.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add beans and cook uncovered until nearly tender, about 5 minutes. Drain well, and set aside in a large bowl.
steps.Step 2: Smash garlic, olive oil, mint, and salt using mortar and pestle.
steps.Step 3: Pour vinegar and half of olive oil mixture over beans and toss well.
steps.Step 4: Transfer beans to a resealable freezer bag. Pour remaining olive oil mixture into bag, squeeze out all air, seal and refrigerate for a minimum of 4 hours.
steps.Step 5: Remove beans from refrigerator, top with fresh mint and serve.

3714.title: Strawberry Crescent Roll Shortcake
3714.description: An easy and delicious breakfast using fresh berries and refrigerated crescents.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
steps.Step 2: Place 1/2 cup strawberries and water in a food processor and process until smooth.
steps.Step 3: Combine 3 tablespoons sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Add pureed strawberries. Cook and stir until strawberry sauce has thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in remaining 2 cups sliced strawberries and lemon juice. Set aside.
steps.Step 4: Unroll dough. Place 1 crescent atop another and roll up, starting at the smallest end, to make 4 double-rolled crescents. Brush each roll with 1/2 teaspoon heavy whipping cream and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
steps.Step 5: Bake crescents until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack and let cool completely.
steps.Step 6: Split each roll in half horizontally and fill with strawberries. Top with 1/2 cup whipped cream and the top half of the crescent roll. Top with more strawberries.

3740.title: Patriotic Berry Trifle
3740.description: A layered dessert featuring angel food cake, berries, pudding, and whipped topping.  A festive and easy-to-make dessert perfect for any patriotic celebration.

steps.Step 1: Prepare the instant pudding according to package directions, mixing with cold milk until soft set. Refrigerate until firmed up.
steps.Step 2: Sprinkle half of the diced angel food cake onto the bottom of a trifle bowl. Set aside some blueberries, strawberries, and raspberries for decoration. Add half of the remaining berries evenly over the cake.
steps.Step 3: Spoon the set pudding on top of the berries.
steps.Step 4: Add the last layer of cake and any remaining berries. Top with frozen whipped topping, spreading gently to create a smooth surface. Use the reserved berries to decorate the top.
steps.Step 5: Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve. Do not make too far in advance as the cake will break down.

3771.title: Aguachile
3771.description: A spicy, cold dish of freshly caught shrimp marinated in a serrano-lime juice mixture, topped with fresh red onions, avocados, and cucumbers. Best served within one hour with tostadas and a Mexican beer.

steps.Step 1: Divide shrimp onto two shallow plates.
steps.Step 2: Blend lime juice, chiles, cilantro leaves and stems, and 1 teaspoon salt in a blender until smooth. Pour 1/2 of the mixture over each plate of shrimp.
steps.Step 3: Cover and marinate in the refrigerator until shrimp turn opaque and white, 15 to 25 minutes.
steps.Step 4: To serve, top each plate with red onion and avocado. Place cucumber around the edges. Sprinkle with remaining salt.

3808.title: Key Lime Cookie Cake
3808.description: An old family recipe and a very simple Mexican dessert. It consists of ordinary vanilla cookies and a sweet and simple lime cream. As a personal note, this dessert is much better chilled and goes great with any hot drink.

steps.Step 1: Pour condensed milk, lime juice, and lime zest into a blender and blend until rich and creamy.
steps.Step 2: Arrange a layer of cookies to cover the bottom of a 9x13-inch glass baking dish. Pour 1/4 of the lime cream over the cookies. Repeat layers to use up all cookies and cream.
