steps.Step 3: Cover and refrigerate for 5 to 6 hours, or if you prefer a more chilled dessert, place in the freezer for 2 hours before serving.

3812.title: Mini Eggplant Pizzettes
3812.description: A delicious and easy lunchtime pizza alternative made with eggplant slices topped with pasta sauce, Canadian bacon (optional), and mozzarella cheese.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven or toaster oven to 425 degrees F.
steps.Step 2: Brush both sides of the eggplant with the oil and season with the salt and pepper.
steps.Step 3: Arrange on a baking sheet and bake until browned and almost tender, 6 to 8 minutes, turning once.
steps.Step 4: Spread 1 tablespoon of pasta sauce on each eggplant slice.
steps.Step 5: Top, if desired, with the Canadian bacon and shredded cheese.
steps.Step 6: Bake until the cheese melts, 3 to 5 minutes.
steps.Step 7: Serve hot.

3879.title: Lemon Strawberry Trifle
3879.description: A delightful trifle featuring strawberries, whipped cream, lemon pudding, and angel food cake.  The perfect balance of rich and fruity.

steps.Step 1: Whisk lemon pudding mixes and almondmilk together for 2 minutes. Fold in 8 oz of whipped topping. Refrigerate for at least 5 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Cut angel food cake into small, bite-sized pieces. Set aside.
steps.Step 3: In a separate bowl, combine remaining 8 oz of whipped topping with lemon curd, folding together again thoroughly combined. Set aside.
steps.Step 4: Layer half of the angel food cake in the bottom of a large bowl or trifle dish.
steps.Step 5: Top with half of the pudding mixture, half of the sliced strawberries, and half of the lemon curd mixture.
steps.Step 6: Repeat layers.
steps.Step 7: Garnish with fresh strawberries and lemon slices if desired.
steps.Step 8: Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

3889.title: Sweet Berry Parfait
3889.description: Creamy yogurt parfaits make deliciously balanced breakfasts or snacks.  Use 2/3 cup yogurt, 1/2 cup chopped fruit, 2 tablespoons crunch, 1 teaspoon drizzle, and 1 teaspoon chopped fresh herb to make your own version.

steps.Step 1: Spoon 1/3 cup yogurt into a 6- to 8-ounce parfait glass or jar.
steps.Step 2: Top yogurt 1/2 half of the blackberries, 1/2 of the almonds, and 1/2 of the honey.
steps.Step 3: Repeat layers with the remaining yogurt, berries, almonds, and honey.
steps.Step 4: Top parfait with thyme.

3891.title: Lamb Korma
3891.description: A traditional Kashmiri Korma recipe, featuring lamb, potatoes, and a flavorful curry sauce.  The recipe is adaptable, with variations in the amount of curry powder and simmering time for the potatoes.

steps.Step 1: Place lamb in a bowl and drizzle 2 teaspoons olive oil over lamb; stir until coated.
steps.Step 2: Heat remaining 2 teaspoons olive oil in a saucepan over low heat; cook and stir onion until softened, 10 to 15 minutes. Remove saucepan from heat and add potato to onion.
steps.Step 3: Heat a large skillet over medium heat; cook and stir lamb, working in small batches, until browned, about 5 minutes per batch. Transfer browned lamb to onion mixture.
steps.Step 4: Stir curry into lamb-onion mixture and cook over medium heat for 1 minute. Add water to lamb-onion mixture and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover saucepan, and simmer until lamb is cooked through and potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Mix coconut milk and chickpeas into lamb-onion mixture and simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes.

3968.title: Air Fryer Salmon Cakes
3968.description: These salmon cakes are flavorful and have little filler, perfect for a quick and easy meal.  The recipe uses fresh salmon for a delicious result.

steps.Step 1: Preheat an air fryer for 10 minutes to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Whisk egg, mayonnaise, parsley, chervil, dill, chives, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, seafood seasoning, and salt together in a bowl. Mix in panko bread crumbs until combined.
steps.Step 3: Gently fold in salmon.
steps.Step 4: Shape mixture into 4 cakes.
steps.Step 5: Line the air fryer basket with perforated parchment.
steps.Step 6: Air-fry salmon cakes for 8 minutes, flipping at the halfway point.
steps.Step 7: Serve immediately.

3971.title: Pineapple Salmon
3971.description: A flavorful and quick salmon dish featuring a sweet and savory pineapple glaze. The salmon is pan-seared and then coated in a delicious mixture of pineapple, teriyaki, and sweet chili sauces.

steps.Step 1: Heat a large saute pan over medium-high heat for 2 minutes. Coat both sides of salmon fillets with cooking spray and add to the hot pan. Cook for 4 minutes. Flip, cover, and cook for 4 minutes more.
steps.Step 2: Whisk water, crushed pineapple, and 1/4 cup teriyaki sauce together in a bowl. Pour sauce over salmon; reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and cook for 2 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Stir pineapple preserves, chili sauce, and remaining 2 teaspoons teriyaki sauce together. Spoon evenly over salmon, cover, and remove from heat. Let stand for 1 to 2 minutes.

3985.title: Sweet Potato Egg Bites
3985.description: Sweet, light, lower-carb breakfast bites featuring eggs and sweet potato.

steps.Step 1: Preheat an air fryer to 375 degrees F (188 degrees C). Spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray.
steps.Step 2: Combine sweet potato, coconut oil, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, and a pinch of salt in a small mixing bowl. Massage the oil and seasonings into the potatoes and transfer to the prepared basket.
steps.Step 3: Air-fry until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes, tossing halfway through to ensure even cooking. The exact amount of time will depend on the size of the cubes. Remove the basket and allow potatoes to cool.
steps.Step 4: While the sweet potatoes are cooling, combine eggs, cottage cheese, liquid egg whites, half-and-half, vanilla, sugar substitute, and a pinch of salt in a blender. Blend on high until well-mixed and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Spray a 7-compartment silicone egg bite mold with cooking spray. Scoop 1 tablespoon sweet potatoes into each compartment and pour egg mixture over top, leaving a little bit of space for expansion. Cover the mold with aluminum foil.
steps.Step 6: Place a trivet into a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot®). Add 1 cup water, and place the egg mold on top of the trivet. Close and lock the lid. Select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 8 minutes. Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build.
steps.Step 7: Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, for 5 minutes, then release remaining pressure using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 5 minutes more. Unlock and remove the lid.

3997.title: Pizza Wheel
3997.description: A delicious combination of mozzarella and provolone cheese, French bread, and sausage. Serve with marinara sauce.

ingredients.name: Johnsonville® Fully Cooked Three-Cheese Italian Style Sausage Rope

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Lightly grease a sheet pan.
steps.Step 2: Remove dough from can, cut in half, and join pieces so long sides are together. Roll the dough out into a square.
steps.Step 3: Place provolone on top of dough. Dice sausage and sprinkle over dough. Top with shredded mozzarella.
steps.Step 4: Roll up and pinch seam to seal. Slice into 8 pieces.
steps.Step 5: Bake until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with marinara dipping sauce.

4017.title: Summer Squash Bake
4017.description: A simple and cheesy side dish featuring zucchini and yellow squash, baked until tender and slightly browned.  Perfect for a summer meal.

ingredients.name: KRAFT Finely Shredded Italian Style Five Cheese Blend

steps.Step 1: Heat oven to 375 degrees F.
steps.Step 2: Cook zucchini and yellow squash in large skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat 5 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
steps.Step 3: Whisk eggs and dressing in large bowl until blended. Stir in Parmesan cheese.
steps.Step 4: Add zucchini mixture and all remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
steps.Step 5: Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
steps.Step 6: Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until center is set and edges are lightly browned.

4030.title: Baked Zucchini Curly Fries
4030.description: Spiralized and breaded zucchini is baked up into a crispy side dish with a little kick.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
steps.Step 2: Combine spiralized zucchini and cornstarch in a bowl and toss to combine.
steps.Step 3: Place beaten eggs in a shallow dish. Stir panko bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, paprika, seasoning salt, cayenne, and garlic powder together in a second shallow dish.
steps.Step 4: Working in batches, lightly dredge zucchini in the eggs, shaking off the excess before dredging in the bread crumb mixture.
steps.Step 5: Spread zucchini out in a single layer on the prepared baking sheets. Spray the top of the zucchini with more nonstick cooking spray.
steps.Step 6: Bake until crispy and golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Serve hot and fresh.

4034.title: Spiced Lamb Pizza
4034.description: This recipe, inspired by a similar one but with modifications, is a delicious spiced lamb pizza. It features a flavorful lamb mixture topped with a flavorful onion-cilantro mix on a pizza crust.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 500 degrees F (260 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Mix onion, cilantro, and lemon juice together in a bowl; set aside.
steps.Step 3: Dust a baking sheet with flour.
steps.Step 4: Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir lamb in the hot skillet until mostly cooked through, breaking into little pieces with the back of a wooden spoon, 5 to 6 minutes.
steps.Step 5: While the lamb is cooking, stretch dough out onto the prepared baking sheet until you get an oval shape. Let rest for 1 minute, and stretch it again if it shrinks.
steps.Step 6: Bake dough in the center of the preheated oven until puffy and mostly cooked, 5 to 7 minutes.
steps.Step 7: Add tomato paste, garlic, cinnamon, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper flakes to the cooked lamb. Mix it all together and cook until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes.
steps.Step 8: Remove dough from the oven and brush with remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add lamb mixture and evenly distribute over the crust.
steps.Step 9: Return pizza to the oven and bake for 2 minutes. Turn on the broiler and broil until crust is golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes longer.
steps.Step 10: Remove pizza from the oven. Transfer to a cutting board and cut into 8 pieces. Top with the onion-cilantro mixture.

4041.title: Cheesy Beef Crescent Roll Pie
4041.description: An easy and satisfying ground beef pie topped with crescent roll crust.  A comforting and flavorful meal.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a cast iron skillet over medium-high heat until beef is browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain and discard grease.
steps.Step 3: Return to medium heat, add spaghetti sauce and diced tomatoes, and season with salt and pepper. Cook until thoroughly heated.
steps.Step 4: Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
steps.Step 5: Unroll crescent dough and arrange triangles over cheese in the skillet.
steps.Step 6: Brush with butter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
steps.Step 7: Bake in the preheated oven until the crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

4056.title: Beefy Pasta Skillet
4056.description: A quick and easy pasta dish featuring ground beef, onion, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, and cheese, simmered with pasta until heated through.

ingredients.name: cooked corkscrew-shaped pasta or elbow pasta

steps.Step 1: Cook beef and onion in skillet until browned. Pour off fat.
steps.Step 2: Add soup, water, Worcestershire, cheese and pasta and heat through.

4073.title: Blueberry Croissant Bread Pudding
4073.description: This is a luxurious, lavish, buttery, and decadent dessert. The top is crunchy and the inside is light and custard-y. Delicious served with a dollop of freshly whipped cream.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 225 degrees F (110 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and spread out croissant cubes on top.
steps.Step 2: Bake in the preheated oven until croissant cubes are very dry, 30 to 35 minutes. Turn off the oven and cool cubes slightly.
steps.Step 3: Lightly spray a 9x13-inch baking dish, add dried croissants, and evenly distribute the blueberries among the croissant cubes.
steps.Step 4: Whisk eggs together in a large bowl. Add milk, heavy cream, sugar, butter, almond extract, cinnamon, and salt; whisk until well blended. Pour the custard mixture over the croissants, and push croissant cubes down with the palm of your hand or a large spatula to fully submerge. Cover the dish and refrigerate for 2 hours to allow the bread to absorb all of the custard.
steps.Step 5: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 6: Bake in the preheated oven, uncovered, until the top is puffed and golden and the custard is set in the center, 40 to 45 minutes.
steps.Step 7: Remove the bread pudding to a rack and let cool for 10 minutes.

4087.title: Easy Grilled Mahi Mahi
4087.description: This grilled mahi mahi is a perfect summer dish, ideal for grilling season and celebrations like the 4th of July. The flavors pair well with a chilled glass of white wine, such as Vinho Verde Estreia.

steps.Step 1: Preheat a gas grill for medium-high heat (450 degrees F (230 degrees C)) and lightly oil the grate.
steps.Step 2: To make the spice mixture: Combine paprika, oregano, cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper, and cayenne in a small bowl.
steps.Step 3: Brush mahi mahi fillets with olive oil on both sides and season with spice mixture.
steps.Step 4: Grill on the hot grill until golden and fish flakes easily with a fork, about 4 to 5 minutes per side.
steps.Step 5: Drizzle with lemon juice and serve.

4123.title: South Carolina Catfish Stew
4123.description: A delicious spicy, tomato-based stew featuring catfish, bacon, potatoes, and onions. This simple recipe is perfect for a comforting meal, and the stew can be kept warm on the stove all day for refills.

steps.Step 1: Combine condensed soup, water, ketchup, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce, butter, and browning sauce in a stockpot over medium heat. Add potatoes, bacon, and onion.
steps.Step 2: Season with thyme, chili powder, salt, and pepper; bring to a boil.
steps.Step 3: Rinse catfish and pat dry. Cut into bite-sized pieces and add to the stockpot.
steps.Step 4: Reduce heat to a simmering boil and cook, covered or uncovered, until onions and potatoes are tender, about 25 minutes.

4191.title: Wheat Dosa
4191.description: Wheat dosa is a South Indian crepe made from whole wheat flour. It's typically served with coconut chutney, sambar, or other Indian curries.
4191.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons oil, salt, and baking soda together in a bowl. Mix for 1 to 2 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Add 1 3/4 cup water and mix until it's lump free, the chunks of flour have dissolved, and the batter has a good consistency, adding more water if needed.
steps.Step 3: Heat 1 tablespoon oil on a griddle over medium heat.
steps.Step 4: Pour some of the batter onto the griddle; spread the batter in a circular motion, slowly yet steadily.
steps.Step 5: Cook until the edges start to brown, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from the grill.
steps.Step 6: Repeat with remaining batter, adding more oil between each batch.

4199.title: Whole Wheat Sourdough Biscuits
4199.description: These are perfectly fluffy and tasty whole wheat sourdough biscuits that go together quick. Perfect for topping a pot pie or putting under sausage and gravy.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
steps.Step 2: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt together into a large bowl. Cut in butter until pea-sized. Add sourdough starter and stir just until dough holds together.
steps.Step 3: Transfer to a floured board and knead 5 to 10 times. Pat to a 3/4-inch thickness and cut into 10 biscuits. Place on the prepared baking sheet.
steps.Step 4: Bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

4203.title: Joyful Chocolate Overnight Oats
4203.description: A fun, yummy, and quick breakfast treat featuring components of a popular candy bar. Kids can mix and top their own breakfast goodies.

steps.Step 1: Mix oats, almond milk, powdered sugar, and cocoa powder in a pint jar or a 12-ounce glass.
steps.Step 2: Cover the jar and refrigerate for at least 8 hours or overnight.
steps.Step 3: Stir the mixture before serving and top with almonds, chocolate chips, and coconut.

4212.title: Buttermilk Sourdough Biscuits
4212.description: These buttermilk sourdough biscuits are made with a sourdough starter, resulting in a lighter and less dense texture than traditional biscuits. The recipe yields 12 servings and requires a longer preparation time due to the sourdough starter.

steps.Step 1: Make buttermilk by combining milk and vinegar in a small bowl. Stir and let sit until slightly thickened and curdled, 5 to 10 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Mix 1 cup flour, sourdough starter, and buttermilk together in a large, non-reactive bowl. Cover and let dough sit in a warm place, 8 hours to overnight.
steps.Step 3: Add 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and baking soda to the dough; knead lightly until well mixed.
steps.Step 4: Turn dough out onto a work surface that has been sprinkled with remaining 1/2 cup flour. Roll or pat dough out to a thickness of about 1/2 inch. Dip a biscuit cutter into melted butter and cut out biscuits.
steps.Step 5: Place biscuits close together in a greased 9x13-inch pan. Cover and let rest for 30 minutes.
steps.Step 6: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).
steps.Step 7: Melt any remaining butter and brush over biscuits.
steps.Step 8: Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes. Serve warm.

4230.title: Zucchini Bread Oatmeal
4230.description: This healthy bowl of oats is packed with zucchini and cinnamon and sweetened with maple syrup. The flavors of zucchini bread are brought to your morning oatmeal.

steps.Step 1: Bring almond milk and salt to a boil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Add oats, zucchini, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
steps.Step 2: Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Remove from heat and stir in maple syrup, butter, and vanilla.
steps.Step 4: Top with crushed walnuts.

4232.title: Creamy Sweet Potato Oatmeal
4232.description: Loaded with sweet potato and warm spices, this oatmeal is a nutritious and tasty breakfast! It's perfect for using up leftover sweet potatoes. Just adjust the sweetener and butter if your recipe already has them.

steps.Step 1: Combine almond milk and salt in a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
steps.Step 2: Add oats, sweet potatoes, flax seeds, cinnamon, ginger, and cloves.
steps.Step 3: Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Remove from heat and stir in honey, butter, and vanilla extract.

4236.title: California Crescent Sandwiches
4236.description: A delicious sandwich made with flaky crescent dough, turkey, bacon, and guacamole.  A satisfying and quick meal.

ingredients.name: Pillsbury® refrigerated crescent dinner rolls or Pillsbury® Crescent Recipe Creations® refrigerated seamless dough sheet

steps.Step 1: Separate or cut dough into 8 squares (if using crescent rolls, press perforations to seal). Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
steps.Step 2: Bake at 375 degrees F 8 to 10 minutes.
steps.Step 3: To serve, spread guacamole on 4 of the rectangles. Top with lettuce, turkey and bacon. Top with remaining rectangles.

4244.title: Spinach Whole Wheat Quesadillas
4244.description: A quick, easy, and light dinner, snack, or appetizer.  This recipe features spinach, cheese, and spices in whole wheat tortillas.

steps.Step 1: Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Place 1 tortilla onto the skillet.
steps.Step 2: Sprinkle about half the Cheddar cheese evenly over the tortilla.
steps.Step 3: Top with the spinach, green onions, garlic powder, and chili powder.
steps.Step 4: Cover with the remaining Cheddar cheese. Place the second tortilla on top.
steps.Step 5: Cook until the bottom tortilla starts to develop a bit of color and starts to crisp, about 3 minutes.
steps.Step 6: To flip and cook the other side, slide the quesadilla off the non-stick pan onto a dinner plate, cover with another dinner plate and flip.
steps.Step 7: The crispy tortilla side should now be on top. Slide the quesadilla back onto the pan and cook until the bottom tortilla starts turning crisp, about 3 minutes more.
steps.Step 8: Slide onto a cutting board, and cut into 8 wedges to serve.

4326.title: Lemon Curd Bars
4326.description: Tangy, fruity lemon bars made easy with prepared lemon curd. Coconut and almonds add richness and texture.

steps.Step 1: Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until creamy.
steps.Step 2: Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
steps.Step 3: Pat 3/4 of mixture into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
steps.Step 4: Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool slightly.
steps.Step 5: Spread curd over baked layer. Add coconut and almonds to remaining crumb mixture; stir to mix.
steps.Step 6: Sprinkle over curd.
steps.Step 7: Bake additional 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
steps.Step 8: Remove from oven and cool slightly. Dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

4332.title: Cranberry Cornmeal Linzer Cookies
4332.description: These delicious cookies feature a tangy cranberry filling nestled between two buttery cornmeal cookies. A Wisconsin-inspired treat, perfect for sharing or gifting!

steps.Step 1: Beat butter and white sugar together until creamy. Beat egg into the mixture.
steps.Step 2: Whisk together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, and salt. Gradually add the flour mixture to the butter mixture, stirring until combined. Beat in vanilla extract.
steps.Step 3: Form the dough into a ball, wrap it tightly in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
steps.Step 4: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease baking sheets.
steps.Step 5: Roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thick. Cut out cookies using round or Linzer cookie cutters. Use a smaller cutter to cut out the center of the tops.
steps.Step 6: Place the cookie bottoms and tops 1 inch apart on the baking sheets.
steps.Step 7: Bake until edges are lightly golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Transfer to wire racks to cool.
steps.Step 8: Stir cranberries, brown sugar, and water together in a saucepan over medium-high heat until cranberries are soft, about 10 minutes.
steps.Step 9: Stir in butter and lemon juice into the cranberry mixture; remove from heat and cool.
steps.Step 10: Spread a small amount of the cranberry mixture onto one side of the bottom half of a cookie. Place the top half of the cookie on top of the cranberry mixture. Repeat with remaining cookies and filling.

4335.title: Sweet Potato Energy Bites
4335.description: These tasty little bites are packed with sweet potato, oats, almond meal, hemp seeds, and almond butter. They're a great protein and energy boost.  They are gluten-free and can be made vegan by replacing honey with maple syrup.
4335.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Place mashed sweet potato, oats, almond meal, hemp seeds, almond butter, honey, cinnamon, vanilla, and sea salt into a bowl and stir until all ingredients are well combined.
steps.Step 2: Refrigerate the mixture for 15 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Roll chilled mixture into about 20 1-inch balls.
steps.Step 4: Place energy balls back into the refrigerator for 15 minutes until set and cold.
steps.Step 5: Store in a covered container in the refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.

4338.title: Vegan Energy Balls
4338.description: These energy balls, made without cocoa powder for a fellow yogi observing Lent, are a delicious and nutritious treat.  They offer a satisfying alternative to chocolate and are perfect for a healthy snack or on-the-go energy boost.
4338.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Combine ground almonds and cinnamon in a small bowl; set aside.
steps.Step 2: Mix almond butter, agave syrup, and protein powder together in a bowl. Add shredded coconut, coconut sap, and nutmeg.
steps.Step 3: Combine pumpkin, flax, and sesame seeds in the bowl of a food processor; pulse until blended. Add to almond butter mixture along with sunflower seeds.
steps.Step 4: Mince dried apple in the food processor. Add to almond butter mixture along with walnuts.
steps.Step 5: Form into 1-inch balls and roll in the almond-cinnamon mixture to coat.
steps.Step 6: Place in the freezer to firm up and store.

4352.title: Lemon Mint Pound Cake
4352.description: A moist and flavorful pound cake infused with lemon and mint, featuring a light and fluffy texture.  Topped with a creamy lemon curd frosting and fresh berries for a delightful dessert.

steps.Step 1: Place sugar and mint in a small food processor; cover and process until blended. Set aside.
steps.Step 2: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.
steps.Step 3: In a large bowl, cream butter and 1-3/4 cups confectioners sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in 4-1/2 teaspoons reserved mint mixture. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add mashed potato flakes alternately with 1/4 cup cream. Stir in lemon juice and peel.
steps.Step 4: Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 60-70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack to cool completely.
steps.Step 5: In a large bowl, beat remaining cream until it begins to thicken. Add 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and 1 tablespoon mint mixture; beat until stiff peaks form. Fold in lemon curd; set aside.
steps.Step 6: In another bowl, combine strawberries and blueberries with remaining mint mixture and confectioners sugar.
steps.Step 7: Cube cake into 2 squares. Layer in glassware starting with a dollop of the cream mixture, a spoonful of berries and a couple cake cubes. Repeat.

4372.title: Super Sausage Gravy
4372.description: A hearty breakfast favorite, this recipe features biscuits served with hot sausage gravy, sure to keep you satisfied until your next meal.

ingredients.name: Bob Evans® Original Recipe Sausage Roll

steps.Step 1: Crumble and cook sausage in large skillet over medium heat until browned.
steps.Step 2: Stir in flour until dissolved.
steps.Step 3: Gradually stir in milk.
steps.Step 4: Cook gravy until thick and bubbly.
steps.Step 5: Season with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 6: Serve hot over biscuits. Refrigerate leftovers.

4373.title: Garlic Mashed Red Potatoes
4373.description: These creamy garlic mashed potatoes are delicious, needing no butter or gravy.  The recipe is simple and perfect for a satisfying side dish.

steps.Step 1: Place potatoes and garlic in a large saucepan; cover with water.
steps.Step 2: Bring to a boil.
steps.Step 3: Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20-25 minutes or until the potatoes are very tender.
steps.Step 4: Drain well.
steps.Step 5: Add the butter, milk and salt; mash.
steps.Step 6: Stir in Parmesan cheese.

4396.title: Hearty Spanish Beef Stew
4396.description: This Spanish beef stew combines elements of ropa vieja and picadillo, creating a hearty and flavorful dish. Serve with cooked rice for a complete meal.

steps.Step 1: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat. Add bell pepper, onion, and garlic. Cook until onions are tender and start to caramelize around the edges, about 5 minutes. Add diced tomatoes.
steps.Step 2: Combine flour, smoked paprika, sweet paprika, oregano, cumin, salt, and pepper in a resealable plastic bag. Add beef stew meat and shake to coat.
steps.Step 3: Heat remaining oil and butter in a skillet over medium-high heat and brown coated beef on all sides, 3 to 5 minutes per side.
steps.Step 4: Transfer browned stew meat to the Dutch oven. Add water and vinegar; stir to combine. Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
steps.Step 5: Remove the lid and add olives. Cook stew for an additional 30 minutes. Adjust seasonings to taste.

4431.title: Mediterranean Red Snapper
4431.description: A simple mixture of parsley, oregano, garlic, and lemon zest brings the flavors of the Mediterranean to fresh whole red snapper. Easy enough for a weeknight meal, yet elegant enough for company!

ingredients.name: whole red snappers, cleaned and scaled

steps.Step 1: Mix parsley, olive oil, oregano, lemon zest, and garlic together in a small bowl.
steps.Step 2: Rinse red snappers and pat dry with paper towels. Cut 3 diagonal slits across the top of each fish, cutting almost to the bone. Season the cavities with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 3: Rub the parsley mixture on the inside and top of the fish, pushing the mixture into the slits. Place the fish in the center of the grill pan; season with salt and pepper.
steps.Step 4: Place the grill pan in the Panasonic Countertop Induction Oven and press "Auto Cook." Select the Fish setting, 3, and 1-pound serving. Cook until an instead-read thermometer inserted into the center reads at least 130 degrees F (54 degrees C), about 20 minutes. Adjust time as needed. Serve with lemon slices.

4435.title: Cinnamon Roll Monkey Bread
4435.description: A true down-south, passed-down recipe that will be enjoyed by everyone. You will be a top Southern cook. If you take this cinnamon roll monkey bread to a work function or church event, they will ask you to make it over and over again.

ingredients.name: refrigerated cinnamon roll dough with icing

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Spray a fluted tube pan (such as Bundt®) with butter-flavored cooking spray.
steps.Step 2: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg together in a bowl.
steps.Step 3: Open the refrigerated cinnamon rolls. Divide rolls by package, then cut into quarters with a pizza/dough cutter.
steps.Step 4: Place each package of cut cinnamon roll pieces in the sugar mixture and toss until covered, keeping them separated. Do not discard excess sugar mixture.
steps.Step 5: Layer each separate portion of sugar-coated cinnamon roll pieces in the bottom of the prepared pan, sprinkling with pecans as you go, ending with pecans on top.
steps.Step 6: Combine excess sugar mixture with 3/4 cup of butter in a saucepan over medium-low heat; bring to a boil. Pour butter mixture over the cinnamon roll pieces.
steps.Step 7: Bake in the preheated oven until the top is crispy, about 40 minutes. Remove and allow to cool for 10 minutes.
steps.Step 8: While cooling, mix confectioners' sugar, lemon-lime beverage, oats, and remaining 1/2 cup of room temperature butter together for icing.
steps.Step 9: Remove the bread from the Bundt® pan, then drizzle the icing over the bread to taste.

4452.title: Easy Slow Cooker Tuna Casserole
4452.description: A simple and easy tuna casserole made in a slow cooker.  This recipe is a variation of a classic tuna casserole, with the option to adjust ingredients for personal preference.

steps.Step 1: Spray a slow cooker with nonstick spray to coat.
steps.Step 2: Combine milk, condensed soup, and garlic in the slow cooker. Stir in tuna, Cheddar cheese, then mushrooms.
steps.Step 3: Add macaroni, season with salt and pepper, and stir to mix.
steps.Step 4: Cover and cook on Low until pasta is very soft, 5 to 6 hours.
steps.Step 5: You can also try cooking it on High for a shorter time. I have used a combination of Low for 3 hours and High for 1 hour, which has also worked.

4474.title: The Best Chocolate Chip Cookies Ever
4474.description: These cookies boast a perfect balance of salty and sweet, with crispy edges and a soft, chewy center. Serve with cold milk for the ultimate treat.

steps.Step 1: Whisk flour, baking powder, salt, and baking soda together in a medium bowl, and set aside.
steps.Step 2: Beat butter and sugars together in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment on medium-high speed until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, scraping down sides of bowl as necessary. Beat for an additional 3 minutes. Add vanilla and beat for 10 seconds.
steps.Step 3: Reduce speed to low and gradually add in the flour mixture, blending just until combined. Fold in chocolate chips.
steps.Step 4: Scoop 1 1/2-inch balls of dough 3 inches apart onto a parchment paper-lined baking sheet; freeze for 15 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (225 degrees C).
steps.Step 6: Bake cookies in the preheated oven, rotating halfway through, until golden around the edges and slightly gooey inside, about 8 minutes. Let stand on the baking sheet for 4 to 5 minutes, then transfer to a cooling rack.

4490.title: Mushroom Lasagna
4490.description: A hearty and flavorful lasagna featuring mushrooms, prosciutto, and a creamy sauce.  Perfect for a satisfying weeknight meal or a special occasion.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking pan.
steps.Step 2: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook 9 lasagna noodles in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Drain.
steps.Step 3: While the noodles are cooking, heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat. Add both mushrooms and onion; cook and stir until tender, 5 to 7 minutes. Add parsley, prosciutto, garlic, and Italian seasoning; cook for 2 minutes longer. Add wine; cook and stir until liquid has evaporated, 3 to 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook until heated through, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Spread sauce in the bottom of the prepared pan. Layer with 3 noodles, 1 1/3 cups sauce, and a scant amount of mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Repeat with the next 2 layers.
steps.Step 5: Combine cream, milk, and remaining mozzarella and Parmesan in a small bowl. Spoon over lasagna.
steps.Step 6: Cover and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes longer. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

4494.title: Pretzel Bread
4494.description: This recipe creates a pretzel bread with a salty brown crust and a tender texture, perfect for sandwiches. The recipe also provides options for making pretzel rolls and chocolate pretzel rolls.

steps.Step 1: Heat milk and butter until warm (100 degrees to 110 degrees F); the butter will not completely melt. Combine with undissolved yeast and brown sugar in a large mixer bowl. Stir in salt and 2 cups flour, beat for 3 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Gradually add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise for 1 hour, or until doubled in size.
steps.Step 4: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
steps.Step 5: Combine boiling solution and bring to a boil.
steps.Step 6: Punch dough down and divide into 2 equal pieces. Form each piece into a tight, smooth ball.
steps.Step 7: Boil each loaf in the solution for 2 minutes, turning after 1 minute.
steps.Step 8: Remove loaves from pot using a slotted spoon and place on a greased baking sheet.
steps.Step 9: Brush with egg wash and cut a cross in the top.
steps.Step 10: Bake for 15 minutes then reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F and bake an additional 10 to 12 minutes until the loaves are evenly browned.
steps.Step 11: Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

4544.title: Raspberry Walnut Baked Brie
4544.description: A simple, elegant appetizer perfect for parties or special occasions.  Puff pastry is folded over brie, raspberry jam, and walnuts for a delightful combination of flavors and textures.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and lightly grease with cooking spray.
steps.Step 2: Lay the puff pastry onto the prepared baking sheet. Center the Brie wheel onto the pastry. Spread the jam evenly over the top of the Brie.
steps.Step 3: Sprinkle the walnuts atop the jam. Fold the puff pastry over the top of the Brie, sealing all openings.
steps.Step 4: Bake in preheated oven until the pastry is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

4548.title: Spicy Hoisin Grilled Broccoli
4548.description: Broccoli tossed in a flavorful sauce with sesame oil, chili oil, hoisin sauce, spices, and grilled in a nonstick grilling skillet. A little char with the sticky spicy sauce is a great change from the normal grilled side dishes.

steps.Step 1: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate.
steps.Step 2: Toss broccoli, sesame oil, hoisin sauce, soy sauce, chili oil, garlic powder, and crushed red pepper together in a bowl. Make sure broccoli is well coated.
steps.Step 3: Add broccoli to a grilling skillet and cook, turning as needed, until lightly browned and fork-tender, about 15 minutes.

4562.title: Moroccan Orange Beef
4562.description: A Moroccan-inspired dish of warming and citrus flavors that really ended up better than I expected. Best served hot over rice.

steps.Step 1: Season beef with 1 teaspoon salt.
steps.Step 2: Heat oil in a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat until shimmering. Sear beef in the hot oil, 3 minutes per side. Remove to a plate.
steps.Step 3: Saute onion and garlic in the Dutch oven until soft, about 5 minutes. Add ginger, allspice, and cinnamon; stir for 1 minute. Pour wine into the pot and bring to a boil while scraping the browned bits of food off the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon. Add water, tomato paste, honey, red pepper flakes, and remaining salt.
steps.Step 4: Cut seared beef into 1-inch cubes and return to the pot. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and let simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Add orange juice, sweetened dried cranberries, mandarin oranges, and prunes; let simmer, uncovered, for another 20 minutes. Serve.

4591.title: Frozen Strawberry Jam
4591.description: A delicious, pectin-free jam made with frozen strawberries.  A simple recipe, perfect for a quick and easy homemade treat.
4591.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Place strawberries in a pot over low heat; add lemon juice. Mash with a potato masher as strawberries thaw.
steps.Step 2: Stir in sweetener when strawberries are the consistency of your liking.
steps.Step 3: Increase heat to medium and bring to a boil. Continue to cook until reduced and thickened, 10 to 15 minutes.
steps.Step 4: While jam cooks, place a small plate in the freezer.
steps.Step 5: Put a small amount of jam on the cold plate and run your finger straight through, dividing it in half.
steps.Step 6: If the mixture runs back together, continue to cook until thickened, 5 to 10 minutes more; if it stays divided, jam is ready to serve.

4622.title: Cheddar Mashed Potatoes
4622.description: A comforting twist on classic mashed potatoes, featuring a creamy texture with cheddar cheese, bacon, and chives. The recipe is quick and easy, perfect for a crowd.

steps.Step 1: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water; cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
steps.Step 2: Cook for 15-20 minutes or until tender. Drain and mash.
steps.Step 3: Add sour cream, butter, salt and pepper; beat until smooth and fluffy.
steps.Step 4: Transfer to a greased 2-1/2-qt. baking dish.
steps.Step 5: Sprinkle with cheese, bacon and chives if desired.
steps.Step 6: Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees F for 20 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

4640.title: Apple Butter Recipe
4640.description: A delicious apple butter recipe that can be easily altered with spices. This recipe uses Honeycrisp and Granny Smith apples, apple cider, sugar, and lemon juice. It's perfect for canning and preserving.

ingredients.name: canning jars with lids and rings

4640.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Combine Honeycrisp apples, Granny Smith apples, and apple cider in a large stainless steel or enamel-coated saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer until mixture reduces by about half, about 20 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Stir sugar and lemon juice into the apple mixture; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, and continue cooking at a simmer until the mixture is very thick, about 25 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Sterilize the jars and lids in boiling water for at least 5 minutes. Pack apple butter into the hot, sterilized jars, filling the jars to within 1/4 inch of the top. Run a knife or a thin spatula around the insides of the jars after they have been filled to remove any air bubbles. Wipe the rims of the jars with a moist paper towel to remove any food residue. Top with lids and screw on rings.
steps.Step 4: Place a rack in the bottom of a large stockpot and fill halfway with water. Bring to a boil and lower jars into the boiling water using a holder. Leave a 2-inch space between the jars. Pour in more boiling water if necessary to bring the water level to at least 1 inch above the tops of the jars. Bring the water to a rolling boil, cover the pot, and process for 10 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Remove the jars from the stockpot and place onto a cloth-covered or wood surface, several inches apart, until cool. Once cool, press the top of each lid with a finger, ensuring that the seal is tight (lid does not move up or down at all). Store in a cool, dark area.

4642.title: Grilled Cuban Bunini Sandwich
4642.description: A flavorful sandwich featuring pulled pork, ham, Swiss cheese, and pickles, all nestled within soft hamburger buns. The recipe uses a slow cooker for the pulled pork, ensuring tenderness, and a panini press for a satisfyingly grilled result.

steps.Step 1: Combine salt, garlic powder, onion powder, cumin, oregano, crushed red pepper, peppercorns, bay leaf, and lime/orange zest and juices in a bowl.
steps.Step 2: Place sliced onions and garlic cloves in the bottom of slow cooker. Top with pork shoulder and pour juice and spice mixture over the meat.
steps.Step 3: Set slow cooker on low for 6 to 8 hours.
steps.Step 4: When done, remove pork from cooker and let cool slightly. Then shred cooked pork into thick chunks using 2 forks.
steps.Step 5: Pour remaining juices over pork to keep warm.
steps.Step 6: Preheat a panini press according to manufacturer's instructions.
steps.Step 7: Spread Dijon mustard on both sides of each hamburger bun.
steps.Step 8: Layer from bottom to top with pickles, red onions, 1/2 cup pulled pork per sandwich, sliced ham and Swiss cheese.
steps.Step 9: Brush outsides of buns with olive oil and place in panini press until cheese is melted.

4645.title: Pumpkin Spice Bread
4645.description: A moist pumpkin bread recipe, described as tasting like pumpkin pie without the crust.  The recipe is at least 40 years old and yields a substantial amount of bread.

steps.Step 1: In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs.
steps.Step 2: Add pumpkin and mix well.
steps.Step 3: Combine dry ingredients; add to the pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
steps.Step 4: Pour into two greased 9-in. x 5-in. x 3-in. loaf pans.
steps.Step 5: Bake at 350 degrees F for 60-65 minutes or until bread tests done.
steps.Step 6: Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack; cool completely.

4685.title: Apple Butter Spice Cake
4685.description: A moist and flavorful cake perfect for any occasion, this recipe features a delicious blend of apple butter and spices. The topping adds a delightful crunch, making it a truly enjoyable treat.

ingredients.name: whole bran cereal or wheat germ

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch pan.
steps.Step 2: Prepare the topping by mixing together the brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and chopped pecans.
steps.Step 3: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
steps.Step 4: Beat butter and sugar together in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy; add eggs one at a time, thoroughly beating each egg into the butter mixture before adding the next. Add apple butter, vanilla, and wheat germ or bran cereal.
steps.Step 5: Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream; mix well after each addition.
steps.Step 6: Pour half the batter into the prepared pan; sprinkle with half of the topping. Pour remaining batter into pan and top with the rest of the topping.
steps.Step 7: Bake in the preheated oven until a tester inserted in the center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

4704.title: Parsnip Vegetable Soup
4704.description: A hearty and flavorful vegetable soup made with parsnips, carrots, leeks, and onions.  The soup is thickened to a desired consistency and topped with sour cream (or other cream alternatives).

steps.Step 1: Melt butter in a large pot over medium-low heat. Add carrot, leek, onion, ginger, and thyme. Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables have softened, about 10 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.
steps.Step 3: Add parsnips and broth and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer until all vegetables are soft, about 15 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Remove from heat.
steps.Step 5: Puree soup with an immersion blender and season with salt, pepper, and nutmeg.
steps.Step 6: Add more broth if soup is too thick.
steps.Step 7: Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

4810.title: Vegan Pumpkin Waffles
4810.description: Kids love to help make these mini vegan heart-shaped waffles. Top with powdered sugar, vegan butter, and/or syrup.

steps.Step 1: Combine almond milk, pumpkin puree, sugar, oil, and vanilla extract in a bowl.
steps.Step 2: Add flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, salt, baking soda, and nutmeg.
steps.Step 3: Stir until well combined.
steps.Step 4: Preheat a 4-inch mini waffle iron according to manufacturer's instructions.
steps.Step 5: Pour in about 2 tablespoons batter per waffle and cook until golden brown, about 5 minutes.

4811.title: Apple Danish Bars
4811.description: A delicious addition to any meal, these apple Danish bars are perfect for breakfast or a dessert.  The combination of flaky Danish dough and sweet apple filling makes for a delightful treat.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 10x15-inch baking pan.
steps.Step 2: Divide egg; set aside egg white for filling.
steps.Step 3: Combine flour and salt in a bowl. Cut in shortening with 2 knives or a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
steps.Step 4: Mix in milk and egg yolk until incorporated. Divide dough into two equal pieces.
steps.Step 5: Pat one piece into the bottom of the prepared pan; set other piece aside.
steps.Step 6: Mix apples, brown sugar, sour cream, flour, butter, and cinnamon together until well combined.
steps.Step 7: Pour over the dough in the pan.
steps.Step 8: Roll or pat remaining dough into a rectangle and place on top of filling.
steps.Step 9: Beat reserved egg white until frothy and brush over dough.
steps.Step 10: Bake until top and bottom are golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
steps.Step 11: Remove from the oven and allow to cool completely, about 30 minutes, before cutting into bars.

4841.title: Shredded Slow Cooker Green Chile Chicken
4841.description: Flavorful shredded chicken cooked all day in a slow cooker with green chiles, lime, and cumin. Perfect for enchiladas, tacos, burritos, or other dishes.

steps.Step 1: Place oil in the bottom of a slow cooker. Add chicken breasts and thighs, 1 can of chile peppers, onion, garlic, cumin, 1/2 of the lime juice, salt, and pepper.
steps.Step 2: Cook on Low until chicken is falling apart, about 8 hours.
steps.Step 3: Remove chicken and shred with 2 forks.
steps.Step 4: Return chicken to the slow cooker. Add remaining chile peppers and lime juice; stir. Test flavor and season with salt and pepper to taste.

4842.title: Slow Cooker Ropa Vieja
4842.description: A flavorful and tender slow-cooked beef dish, perfect for a satisfying meal.  Pairs well with lime-cilantro cauliflower rice for a low-carb option.

steps.Step 1: Heat avocado oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat; cook beef roast in the hot oil until browned, about 4 minutes per side.
steps.Step 2: Transfer roast to a slow cooker. Pour tomatoes and beef broth over roast; add onions and bell peppers.
steps.Step 3: Mix tomato paste, garlic, olive oil, vinegar, cumin, and salt together in a bowl; pour over onions and bell peppers.
steps.Step 4: Cook on High for 1 hour. Decrease heat to Low and cook until beef is tender enough to shred, about 8 hours.
steps.Step 5: Remove beef from slow cooker and shred on a work surface using 2 forks. Return shredded beef to slow cooker; add cilantro and stir.
steps.Step 6: Cook on Low for 1 hour more.

4881.title: Curried Sweet Potato Mash
4881.description: Sweet potatoes get spiced up! These mashed potatoes are absolutely wonderful with added ginger, roasted garlic, caramelized onions, coconut oil, and a dash of turmeric and curry. Creme fraîche adds a creamy texture and offsets the textures of the onions and garlic.

steps.Step 1: Heat butter and olive oil in a skillet over medium heat; stir in onion and garlic. Reduce heat to low and saute until onions are soft and clear but not toasted, 10 to 15 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Pierce potatoes with a fork. Microwave 3 at a time on high power until tender, but not overdone, 5 to 6 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Mash and mix sweet potatoes with onion-garlic mixture, ginger, creme fraiche, curry powder, turmeric, and pepper until well combined.

4919.title: Cocoa Powder Chocolate Mousse
4919.description: This mousse served in shot glasses is perfect for when you're craving something sweet but just want a small portion. You can enjoy them as soon as you make them, or you can chill them in the fridge for a cooler dessert.

steps.Step 1: Combine heavy whipping cream, cocoa powder, powdered sugar, vanilla extract, and salt a large bowl and beat with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
steps.Step 2: Pipe mousse into 6 shot glasses. Serve immediately or chill until serving.

4946.title: Panettone French Toast Casserole
4946.description: This casserole uses Italian sweet bread, panettone, for a unique twist on a classic American breakfast.  Soaking the bread overnight ensures a light and fluffy texture, best served with warm maple syrup.

steps.Step 1: Combine cream cheese and brown sugar in a stand mixer; beat until smooth and creamy. Add vanilla and salt; beat until incorporated.
steps.Step 2: Beat in eggs one at a time, then gradually add milk and 1 cup of cream, beating on low speed.
steps.Step 3: Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish and arrange panettone slices in overlapping rows. Pour the cream cheese-egg mixture over the slices and gently shake the dish to distribute.
steps.Step 4: Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours to overnight.
steps.Step 5: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Uncover the dish, brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.
steps.Step 6: Bake for 30 minutes, rotate the dish 180 degrees, and bake for 30 more minutes, or until the custard is set in the center. Cover with foil during the last 10 minutes of baking to prevent overbrowning.
steps.Step 7: Meanwhile, beat remaining heavy cream and powdered sugar until semi-firm peaks form. Serve warm with whipped cream, raspberries, and almonds.

5008.title: Lemon Turkey Soup
5008.description: A light and flavorful turkey soup infused with lemon, perfect for using leftover turkey and keeping meals healthy. This guilt-free option is a delicious way to enjoy turkey after holiday indulgence.

steps.Step 1: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and cook until fragrant, about 2 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Add carrots, celery, and bell pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until carrots soften, 8 to 10 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Add stock and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer until flavors blend, about 20 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Add turkey, lemon zest, and juice to the pan. Simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Add spinach, salt, and black pepper to taste. Simmer until spinach wilts and turns bright green, 1 to 2 minutes more.

5035.title: Turkey Lumpia
5035.description: This twist on a Filipino favorite is a delicious appetizer or party treat. Enjoy with sweet chili sauce for dipping.

steps.Step 1: Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper.
steps.Step 2: Combine turkey, egg, onion, garlic, cumin, Creole seasoning, salt, and pepper in a bowl. Mix well with your hands.
steps.Step 3: Position a wonton wrapper on a cutting board so it looks like a diamond. Spread a heaping teaspoonful of the turkey mixture in a horizontal line across the bottom third of the wrapper. Fold over the bottom corner and roll once. Fold over the two side corners and roll again to secure. Dampen the top corner with a little cool water. Roll up and press to seal.
steps.Step 4: Place the roll on the prepared cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining rolls, arranging them in a single layer. Freeze until ready to fry.
steps.Step 5: Heat oil in a deep-fryer or large saucepan to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 6: Fry the lumpia in batches, about 3 minutes per batch. Remove from the oil and cut in half. Fry again for 30 seconds. Drain on paper towels.

5101.title: Michigan Hot Dogs
5101.description: Simple hot dogs prepared Michigan style.  Serve with dill pickle-flavored potato chips or French fries for extra flavor.

steps.Step 1: Place hot dogs in a large stockpot. Cover with water and bring to a boil. Turn heat off, cover, and let sit.
steps.Step 2: Heat a skillet over medium-high heat, add ground beef and half of the diced onions. Cook and stir until beef is no longer pink; making sure to break into fine pieces, about 8 minutes.
steps.Step 3: Meanwhile, whisk water, ketchup, tomato paste, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, and chili powder until smooth.
steps.Step 4: Drain ground beef mixture and return to the skillet. Stir in reserved ketchup mixture, reduce heat, and simmer for 10 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Place hot dogs in buns. Top hot dogs with beef mixture. Divide remaining onions on top of the beef mixture and garnish with mustard.

5121.title: Spinach Madeline
5121.description: Spinach Madeline is a quick and easy spinach side dish spiced with jalapeño. It is creamy and cheesy and the seasoned bread crumbs give it a little crunch factor. A delicious addition to your Thanksgiving table!

steps.Step 1: Melt butter in a skillet over low heat. Add bread crumbs. Cook and stir until butter is incorporated into the bread crumbs. Remove from skillet and set aside.
steps.Step 2: Place spinach in a microwave-safe baking dish. Add water. Cover and cook on high for 7 1/2 minutes, stirring halfway through. Drain over a measuring cup. Add enough evaporated milk to make 1/2 cup. Set aside.
steps.Step 3: Melt butter in the skillet. Add flour and cook, stirring continuously, until mixture turns paste-like. Add onion and cook, stirring constantly until soft and translucent, 4 to 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Slowly add milk mixture, stirring constantly. Mix in cheese, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper. Add spinach and cook until well incorporated, 2 to 3 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Set an oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler.
steps.Step 5: Place spinach mixture in a small greased baking dish, top with bread crumbs, and place under the broiler until bread crumbs are golden, about 5 minutes.

5122.title: Meatless Black Bean Burgers
5122.description: These meatless burgers are a favorite for those who enjoy meatless Mondays.  They're made with black beans, various vegetables, and spices, and are served on toasted buns with a special aioli sauce and cheese.

steps.Step 1: Puree black beans in a food processor, or mash with a fork.
steps.Step 2: Combine bread crumbs, bell peppers, onion, eggs, barbecue sauce, nutritional yeast, salt, olive oil, taco seasoning, black pepper, garlic powder, chili powder, and chili sauce in a large mixing bowl. Add mashed beans and mix well.
steps.Step 3: Form mixture into 8 patties. Place on greased waxed paper and let sit in the refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours.
steps.Step 4: Lightly grease a cast iron griddle pan with vegetable oil and heat over medium heat. Add burgers and fry until cooked through, 3 to 5 minutes per side.
steps.Step 5: While burgers are cooking, mix mayonnaise, vegan bacon bits, relish, vinegar, and tomato paste for aioli together in a small bowl.
steps.Step 6: Top each burger with a slice of Monterey Jack cheese. Serve on toasted hamburger buns with aioli sauce.

5157.title: Baja Baked Chicken Cheeseburgers
5157.description: These baked chicken burgers showcase the flavors of Baja California.  A delicious and easy recipe perfect for a satisfying meal.

steps.Step 1: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
steps.Step 2: Slice half of the jalapeno pepper, bell pepper, and onion into rings for topping. Set aside.
steps.Step 3: Combine ground chicken and cilantro in the bowl of a food processor; season with adobo seasoning, cumin, and Mexican seasoning. Add remaining peppers and onion. Pulse until mixture is combined. Shape into 8 burgers.
steps.Step 4: Place burgers on a rimmed baking sheet lined with a drip tray.
steps.Step 5: Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 160 degrees F (70 degrees C). Place 1 slice of pepper Jack cheese on top of each burger. Add onion, bell pepper, and jalapeno slices on top.
steps.Step 6: Spread Mexican sour cream onto each hamburger bun. Top with a chicken burger and serve immediately.

5164.title: Red Curry Butternut Squash
5164.description: A sweet, spicy, and flavorful red curry butternut squash dish. A turkey-friendly side dish that is a delicious and easy-to-make meal.
5164.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Chop green onions, reserving about 1 tablespoon chopped green onion tops for garnish. Heat vegetable oil in a Dutch oven or heavy saucepan over medium heat; saute larger portion of green onions, tomato paste, red curry powder, cumin, and red curry paste in the hot oil until green onions and seasonings sizzle and give off a toasted smell, about 5 minutes.
steps.Step 2: Stir garlic into green onion mixture; saute until garlic is fragrant, about 1 more minute.
steps.Step 3: Pour coconut milk into Dutch oven and stir until thoroughly combined. Mix fish sauce and brown sugar into coconut milk sauce, stirring to dissolve brown sugar. Bring sauce to a simmer.
steps.Step 4: Stir butternut squash cubes into sauce, turn heat to medium-low, and cover with a lid. Gently stir every 5 minutes until squash are tender, about 20 minutes. Watch carefully, squash overcooks easily.
steps.Step 5: Stir basil leaves into butternut squash. Taste for salt and spiciness and adjust seasoning if needed. Transfer to a serving dish and sprinkle with reserved green onions.

5209.title: Sweet Peach Crepe Filling
5209.description: A delicious, rich, light peach and cream filling for crepes.  Serve with iced coffee, orange juice, or water. Can be served hot or cold.

steps.Step 1: Drain ricotta cheese in cheesecloth placed over a bowl, 12 to 24 hours.
steps.Step 2: Combine drained ricotta, confectioners' sugar, cinnamon, vanilla extract, and nutmeg in a large bowl. Refrigerate immediately.
steps.Step 3: Spread peach pie filling into the bottom of a nonstick pot and add lemon juice. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring with a heat-resistant rubber spatula, until steam or bubbles begin to form. Use the spatula to roll filling together into the middle of the pan, and spread again. Repeat this process until filling is the consistency of honey.
steps.Step 4: While filling is still hot, scrape into a container and allow to cool, 20 to 30 minutes.
steps.Step 5: Take the cream filling out of the refrigerator. Combine fruit mixture with cream in a separate bowl, 1 spoonful of each at a time, until the consistency is that of cake frosting. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

5226.title: Vegan Skillet Apples
5226.description: Lightly sweetened apples in a thick sauce cooked in a skillet without butter. These make a quick dessert that can be served alone or with vegan ice cream. They are even better the next day. I like to use them in crepes, on pancakes, or topped with a crumble and crisped up under the broiler.
5226.cholesterol: (-) Information is not currently available for this nutrient.

steps.Step 1: Heat a large skillet over medium-low heat. Peel and core apples. Cut them into quarters, then each quarter into 3 pieces. Add apples to the skillet immediately after they are cut.
steps.Step 2: Add 1/4 cup water, muscovado sugar, jam, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Mix to combine all ingredients and to coat apples evenly. Cover and cook until tender, about 10 minutes. Do not open the lid during this time. Shake the skillet to stir around the apples but do not stir them with utensils.
steps.Step 3: Stir 1 teaspoon water and cornstarch together in a small bowl. Pour slurry into the apples and stir until creamy. Remove from heat. Allow to cool for 5 minutes before serving.

5244.title: Apple Pie Baked Oatmeal
5244.description: This warmly spiced baked oatmeal, inspired by apple pie flavors, is a hearty and nutritious breakfast or brunch option.  It's easily customizable and can be made ahead for the week.

steps.Step 1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly grease an 11x7-inch baking dish.
steps.Step 2: Toast oats in a skillet until browned and nutty. Add spices and toast for another 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a bowl and cool slightly.
steps.Step 3: Combine cooled oats with 3/4 cup pecans, baking powder, and salt.
steps.Step 4: Melt 3 tablespoons butter and whisk in 6 tablespoons brown sugar. Add milk, egg, and vanilla. Stir in oat mixture and half of the diced apples.
steps.Step 5: Spoon mixture into the prepared pan and bake for 35-40 minutes until golden brown and set.
steps.Step 6: While oatmeal bakes, saute remaining butter, apples, remaining brown sugar, and maple syrup until apples soften and liquid thickens.
steps.Step 7: Spoon apple mixture over baked oatmeal and sprinkle with remaining pecans.

5245.title: Caramel Apple Oatmeal
5245.description: This brown butter caramel oatmeal is a fun and inventive way to get kids to enjoy a hearty breakfast.  Top with whipped topping for extra creaminess, or let kids customize their toppings.

steps.Step 1: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add apple and 1/4 cup brown sugar; cook and stir until browned, about 2 minutes. Transfer to a small serving bowl.
steps.Step 2: Melt remaining butter in a small pot over medium heat. Add remaining brown sugar and stir until dissolved. Add 2 cups heavy cream; bring to a simmer. Add oats, flax seeds, and cinnamon; mix and stir until oats are full cooked and creamy, about 2 minutes, adding a touch more heavy cream if needed.
steps.Step 3: Serve in a bowl topped with caramel apple, raisins, and almonds. Add a spoonful of whipped topping to add additional creaminess.

3485.title: Sloppy Joe Sandwiches
3485.description: A quick, easy, and inexpensive recipe for sloppy joe sandwiches. Brown sugar adds sweetness, and the beef mixture can be served over rice, biscuits, or baked potatoes in addition to buns.

steps.Step 1: Cook beef over medium heat in a saucepan until no longer pink; drain.
steps.Step 2: Stir in ketchup, water, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt.
steps.Step 3: Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 30-40 minutes.
steps.Step 4: Serve on buns.
